ng a 25% increase in\u000aleads and enhancing brand visibility by 30%.\u000aJuly 2022 - August 2023\u000aVARUN RAJ MUKTHALA\u000aPatancheru, sangareddy• +91-8187027805 • varunmudiraj122@gmail.com\u000aLinkedin - https://www.linkedin.com/in/varun-raj-7777a0275\u000aCrafted targeted market strategies, increasing campaign reach by 35% across digital platforms.\u000aConducted advanced market analysis, identifying trends that enhanced market positioning by\u000a25%.\u000aCreated and optimized digital marketing ad campaigns, achieving a 22% increase in conversion\u000arates across multiple platforms.\u000aChief Marketing Officer , Valuu Hub Solutions \u000aApril 2025 – Present\u000aEDUCATION\u000aBachelor of commerce (Business Analytics) - 85%\u000aAvinash College of Commerce\u000a2022 - 2025\u000aSECONDARY SCHOOL - MEC - 87%\u000aAvinash college of commerce\u000a2020 - 2022\u000a10th - SSC- 92%\u000aVidyanikethan high school\u000a2011 - 2020\u000a\u000aADDITIONAL INFORMATION\u000aTechnical Skills: Content Creation , Creatives design, Canva , Social media marketing, Digital\u000amarketing, Wordpress, Content Editing, SEO, Meta ads , performance Marketing.\u000aSoft Skills: Communication , Analytical Thinking, Problem-Solving, Creative thinking, .\u000aCertifications: Foundations of Digital marketing - Google, Advanced Google analytics, Digital\u000amarketing professional - MTF, Excel skills for Business -Goldman Sachs.'),NULL);
INSERT INTO candidates VALUES(833,9,NULL,'MUNIPALLE RAJESH KUMAR','munipalle.rajeshkumar@gmail.com','94',NULL,NULL,'Meticulous Sr Executive Assistant with over 15 years of experience in managing C-level office operations, demonstrating strong capabilities in strategic planning, project management, data analysis, and comprehensive communication. Possesses proficiency in various IT tools including AI, and a proactive approach to operational excellence and decision support.','pending','row_17','2025-11-20 11:53:50','2025-11-25 11:00:55','+91-7093744752',NULL,NULL,unistr('MUNIPALLE RAJESH KUMAR\u000aCareer Summary:\u000aMeticulous task-driven Sr Executive Assistant with over 15 years of professional experience in managing customer\u000aand client-centric office operations. Equipped with exceptional ability to facilitate all aspects of internal and external\u000acommunications, support the day to day Administrative, HR, IT, Project Management financial and operational\u000afunctions by working collaboratively with C- Level executives. Proven talent for aligning business objectives with\u000acomprehensive administrative knowledge to achieve maximum operational impacts, conserve time and boost\u000aefficiency.\u000aACADEMIC DETAILS\u000a PG Diploma (Pursuing Psychology) - Indian Institute of Skill Development and Training\u000a MBA – IIBM (International Institute of Business management)\u000a M.COM – International Trade & Foreign Exchange – Chennai, India\u000aPROFESSIONAL IT CERTIFICATIONS\u000a Post-Graduation Diploma in Software Technologies from NCC – PACE Computer Education, New Delhi with\u000aA+ Grade (PGDST).\u000a Proficiency in IT tools - Microsoft 365, collaboration platforms (MS -Teams, Zoom), MS – Office, Outlook\u000aCalendar, Google Calendar, Share point Google Sheets, Workday, Jira, Chat GPT, Generative AI, SAP (Concur)\u000aTableau, SAP (Field glass ) Power BI.\u000aEXECUTIVE EXPERIENCE DETAILS\u000aSr .Executive Assistant - Global IT Delivery Manager (UK and US) (Oct 2021 to June 2025) HCL\u000a Maintaining UK and US Outlook Calendar of Managing Director in HCL, and End to End Support of\u000aTravel (SAP Concur) and Hotel Accommodation, Plan, Coordinate and Scheduling Meetings, to C – Level\u000aExecutives and Global IT Delivery Manager, Supporting the Director in all the aspects of business and be a\u000apart of team who act as a SPOC for the Delivery Manager.\u000a Ready to Travel to Domestic and International locations on short notice, Coordinate the Catering for\u000athe company, including daily lunch services, Co- ordinate with the Facilities Management Teams, House\u000aKeeping Management teams and all Executives about the requirements of the office requirements\u000a Coordinate with Internal and External Business Meetings with client, customer, vendors and\u000aStakeholders, Jira ticket raising for any technical issues, Time compliance reports, Time sheet maintenance,\u000aCoordinating with International Stake holders, Clients, customers on behalf of Director’s and VP’s,\u000aAdministration activities, claims, expenses of all travel.\u000a International and domestic travel bookings and Conduct regular 1-on-1 meetings with direct reports to\u000adiscuss performance, goals, and address individual concerns, and re-align team goals, as necessary.\u000a Coordinate with external service providers and contractors to resolve problems in a timely manner.\u000aOversee the procurement, distribution, and maintenance of office supplies and utilities.\u000a Supervise housekeeping staff and ensure adherence to Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) for\u000amaintenance.\u000a Project Management / Program Management- Proficiency in project management methodologies, and\u000atools to effectively plan, and execute strategic projects and initiatives\u000a Support in development of Project Management frameworks (Agile), providing suitable training and coaching\u000ato Product Owners, Analysts, Tech Assurance and other project team members.\u000a Data Analysis - Strong analytical skills including statistical analysis, trend identification, and forecasting, to\u000asupport strategic decision-making.\u000a Project Support - Support in project delivery for key projects that span across Product Areas as identified,\u000aconnecting and engaging the right people for projects and managing through to delivery.\u000amunipalle.rajeshkumar@gmail.com\u000arajeshkumar.munipalle@gmail.com\u000a+91-7093744752\u000a+91-9866859925\u000ahttps://www.linkedin.com/in/munipalle-sai-rajesh-\u000a9b952643/\u000a\u000a Presentation Skills - Ability to effectively communicate and discuss strategic initiatives with relevant\u000astakeholders and Vendors\u000a Coordinate with Cross functional heads and Teams for execution of strategic projects envisioned by the\u000aleadership for their respective functions\u000a Client & Customer Management (Internal): Coordinate the daily calendars of senior managers, plan\u000aappointments, and events. Schedule and organize client and other meetings.\u000a Support senior managers to ensure their needs are met, and assist colleagues in managing internal\u000arelationships.\u000a Act as the primary point of contact for colleague requests, scan for urgency and confidentiality, answer,\u000aredirect, monitor, and follow-up.\u000a Maintain and update and event calendars. Code and organize all relevant project documents, managing the\u000aarchiving process in Google Drive.\u000a I can travel along with CEO, or MD for International and Domestic as required, Coordinating with all the\u000aVerticals, of various levels of management within an organization. Managers at different levels are free to\u000afocus on different aspects of the business, from strategic thinking to communicating information to\u000aoperational efficiency.\u000a Coordinate the daily calendars of senior managers, plan appointments, and events. Schedule and organize\u000aclient and other meetings.\u000a Familiar with Project Management Activities like Tracking, coordinating, follow-ups, feedbacks, generating\u000areports, dashboards creating with Jira tool.\u000a Handled different Time zones and Manage US, UK and Germany clients, Customers, Vendors and\u000aStakeholders for business meetings. Experience in managing Virtual Executive Assistants.\u000a Coordinating with the People management includes the organizational mission and goals, workforce\u000arecruitment, compensation, benefits, employee motivation and engagement, communication, and training.\u000a Hands on Experience in managing the International Correspondence, Client Presentations, Coordinating with\u000aFinance and Accounts department regarding the settlements of CEO’s claims, travel expenses and\u000asettlements.\u000a Support the CEO primarily and provide additional support to executive team members, as directed, to ensure\u000athat company goals and objectives are accomplished and that operations run efficiently\u000a Also Coordinates with Internal Heads, Directors, CEO’s, CFO, COO and Managers for the Work completion and\u000aBusiness Reports. Handling personal files and records. Responsible for end-to-end administration process,\u000astrategic, people management, and vendor relationship building. Handling Project Status reports, MIS and\u000aQuarterly Business Reports.\u000a First point of contact for all stakeholders and expected to solve routine/ lower-level issues & offer support to\u000astakeholders - escalate only major requirements to MD to avoid time wastage and close all call to actions from\u000aprevious meeting.\u000a SAP Concur – Travel booking, Keeping a track of all Claims, Expenses, bills and ensuring timely payments &\u000aarranging accommodation of the CEO & the leadership team.\u000a Organizes, plans, and coordinates the logistical support needed for meetings, conferences, internal seminars,\u000aworkshops. Handle expense reports and reimbursement requests for the MD. Keep track of expenses and\u000abudget. Schedule individual and group teleconferences and webinars, Manage procurement and distribution of\u000aall program materials\u000a Ensures that all administrative forms, reports, processes, and audits are completed accurately, timely, and in\u000acompliance with applicable laws /regulations.\u000a Manage inventory of classroom supplies and materials, coordinate activities of program instructors and\u000afacilitators, coordinate global training logistics for multiple trainer and locations for in-person training\u000aexecutions, Publish updates on project execution and completion in the ERP system in a timely manner.\u000a Manage all types of daily correspondence to ensure professional, accurate, and timely responses and\u000aappropriate prioritization. Email control of MS Outlook 365 on behalf of CEO.\u000a Compile receipts/invoices to file the expense reports and work with Finance team for reimbursement\u000a Communicating and co-ordination with Global offices for meeting with other business heads.\u000a Develop project deliverable (presentations, status updates) that help shaping the firm''s strategy by\u000aperforming analysis to deliver relevant and insightful management information, as well as assist in business\u000aplanning and development.\u000a Coordinate for weekly, monthly, quarterly and annual reviews for the CEO’s office with all stakeholders.\u000a Assist the Leadership Team with reporting, headcount management, financial budgeting, in partnership p with\u000aFinance and People and Culture teams, decision-making, program management, and initiative implementation\u000aSr Executive Assistant to Co-Founder & CEO (Singapore) (Mar 2020 to Oct 2021) Techno focus\u000a Develop project deliverable (presentations, status updates) that help shaping the firm''s strategy by\u000aperforming analysis to deliver relevant and insightful management information, as well as assist in business\u000aplanning and development.\u000a Coordinate for weekly, monthly, quarterly and annual reviews for the CEO’s office with all stakeholders.\u000a\u000a Represent the CEO when they are not available and providing a bridge for communication between the Sr.\u000aleadership teams & Stakeholders.\u000a Assist the Leadership Team with reporting, maintaining Calendar Management to CEO,headcount\u000amanagement, financial budgeting, in partnership p with Finance and People and Culture teams, decision-\u000amaking, program management, and initiative implementation\u000a Co-ordinating with Cross Functional Teams to ensure deliverables are met. Wwork Closely coordination with\u000aIndia and US based Directors (stakeholders)\u000aSr Executive Assistant—Reporting to Director (India) (June 2017 to Jan 2020) Capgemini\u000a Preparing presentations, scheduling meetings, maintaining Calendar Management to CEO. Exposure to expat\u000adelegates, interaction with foreign Delegates. Drafting of Letters, Correspondences from the clients can\u000ahandle independently. Co-coordinating Training & Development activities. Visa and travel follow ups and\u000aassistance for the Directors and CEO.\u000a Handling correspondence and follow up the issues (email, Letter Drafting, fax, outlook Express, Travel\u000aBooking, Hotels and Giving Complete support to HR and Admin, Operation Activities)\u000a Maintain Time Sheet Management, Project Documentations, Project Tracking and Monitoring. Conducting\u000aReview meeting on every week for the status.\u000a Responsible for coordinating and supporting PMO activities, Extensive experience with core PM tools including\u000aMicrosoft Project, Microsoft Teams, Share Point, Microsoft OneNote, Microsoft Office Professional (Outlook,\u000aWord, Excel, Visio, Access, etc.).\u000a Ability to provide regular reports both verbal and statistical showing status of ongoing projects\u000a Conducts meetings with clients and CMS internal resources to drive project goals and communicate status.\u000a Ability to provide regular reports both verbal and statistical showing status of ongoing projects\u000a Responding the Customer Queries, issues and monitoring the Sales Review of all the Channel Managers &\u000aRegional Managers.\u000a Vendor & inventory management. All Invoices, travel and expenses bill processing.\u000a Expense Management - Processing Expenses for the Team, classification of expenses, booking of expenses\u000a(codes management).\u000a Inventory Management Maintains appropriate inventory levels of office supplies by checking stock and\u000aanticipating needed supplies, placing and expediting orders for supplies, verifying receipt of supplies and\u000acontrolling of disbursement.\u000a Maintains an effective relationship with customers, team members, and executive management\u000a Plan and coordinate administrative procedures and systems and devise ways to streamline processes. Monitor\u000acosts and expenses to assist in budget preparation\u000a Respond promptly to manager’s queries. Experience exercising discretion and confidentiality with sensitive\u000acompany information. Excellent organizational skills with an ability to think proactively and prioritize work\u000a Assisting the CEO and Partner in identifying and evaluating new opportunities, preparing project reports and\u000apresentations. Preparing business proposals to clients. Ready for 100% Travel on short notice.\u000aSr Executive Assistant- Reporting to Sr Partner (Mar 2013 to May 2017) Deloitte\u000aJob role: & responsibilities\u000a Maintaining Calendar Management to CEO, follow up and Maintain CEO & Partners Time Sheet, Travel\u000aExpenses, in SAP Net viewer, raising draft invoices in SAP, Handling end to end travel of CEO and Partner,\u000atracking approvals, issuance of tickets and hotel accommodations, expenses settlement, typing, distributing\u000aminuets of meeting and Track to closure of all action items.\u000a Check & reply all e-mails on daily basis, in order to make sure no mail remain non-responded by the end of\u000athe business day. Maintain relation with clients.\u000a Can handle independently outlook, Schedule Management, Expense Management, Time sheet management,\u000aTravel Management, E Data Management and Visitors management.\u000a Experience working in a team-oriented, collaborative environment. Booking meetings rooms, organizing\u000ameetings, co-coordinating diaries only for Partners and CEO meeting.\u000a Distributing mails, making personals bills such as Travel, petrol, Hotel and submitting it to Accounts\u000adepartment on time. Adept at handling day to day activities in co-ordination with internal/external\u000adepartments for smooth business operations. Conserve the time by reading, researching, transcribing,\u000aanalyzing information and initiating communications\u000a Deal with corporate presentations and reviews, planning for his business meetings; frequently travel with CEO\u000aand Partners for Business Meetings all over the India.\u000a Provide project management support for on-time delivery of programs at various levels of governance (Team\u000ameetings, senior management updates, Town halls, working groups).\u000a Having Good problem resolving and organizing skills. Develop PowerPoint presentations and other graphic\u000apresentations, type various correspondences both in own signature and in managers signature.\u000a\u000aExecutive Assistant- Reporting to VP (Ops) (Sep 2007 to March 2013) Karvy, India\u000aJob role & Rresponsibilities:\u000a Coordinating with all Channel Managers, Regional Managers, Team Managers, and Project Managers through\u000aOnline Team Viewers Software and Tableau Software for Business Presentations, Business Analysis.\u000a maintaining Calendar Management to CEO ,Office correspondence through e-mail, Data Management &\u000astoring etc. Provide support to VP & AGM by coordination with Top Management Team.\u000a Monitors all CRM modules for the generating of monthly and quarter reports. Monitor inventory of office\u000asupplies and the purchasing of new material with attention to budgetary constraints,\u000a Responsible of all CRM monitoring of sales team, and their day-to-day activities to entry on CRM module for\u000aupdating.\u000a Provide assistance/ Preparation of Presentation for Meetings. Day to day coordination with various\u000adepartments and administrative functions. Daily mail update based on the reports from various dept.\u000a Maintain a professional filing system, both electronically and manually, to support the information and\u000amanagement needs of the business. Coordination with project team members to obtain info regarding\u000aProjects, checking of Purchase & Work Orders and customers documents before getting them approved from\u000aVice President.\u000aAchievements\u000a Best Appreciation Award: Received award from Head of HR & Operations for Assignment in Deloitte\u000aInternational\u000aCorporate Social Responsibility:\u000a Volunteer: Participated in Deloitte IMPACT Day for continues 4 years with NGO’s Organization for programs\u000alike education and mid-day meal. Presently full time participating with Sri Sathya Sai Seva Trust Organization\u000aas a Volunteer for Coordinating the Medical camps, Dropout of Children, Vidya Vahini educational\u000aprogrammers, Motivational programs for IT, ITES and BPO Companies\u000a Conducted and organized Blood Donation Camps in Sathya Sai Seva organization as a Program Coordinator.\u000a\u000aDear Hiring manager,\u000aI am Immediate Joiner and ready to travel international and domestic as required.\u000aI am excited to be applying for the Executive Assistant position in your company. It’s clear that you’re looking for\u000asomeone who understands the nuances of managing a CEO busy day and can proactively tackle issues. As someone\u000awith a sharp eye for detail and a drive to organize, I thrive on making sure every day has a clear plan and every plan\u000ais clearly communicated.\u000aDuring previous role at HCL, Deloitte, and Capgemini as a executive assistant to two of the companies five executive\u000ateam members including CEO.\u000aI was praised for my time management skills, written skills and commitment to excellence.\u000aFrom my 15 years of experience as an EA, I understand the importance of being proactive. In addition to being an\u000aexpert at scheduling meetings, preparing agendas, and managing travel arrangements, I have also developed the\u000aability to anticipate road block and create effective alternative plans. My greatest value to any executive is my ability\u000ato work.\u000aThank you for your time and consideration. I am looking forward to learning more details about the EA position in\u000ayour company.\u000aThanking you\u000aYou’re sincerely\u000aMunipalle Rajesh Kumar.\u000a7093744752, 9866859925'),NULL);
INSERT INTO candidates VALUES(834,9,NULL,'GALI ROHITH KUMAR','gali.rohith63@gmail.com','48',NULL,NULL,'City Operations Manager with experience managing multi-outlet operations, team leadership, and process improvement. Adept at data analysis, business process optimization, and leading large teams to deliver efficiency and customer satisfaction.','pending','row_18','2025-11-20 11:53:50','2025-11-25 11:00:55','+91 83176 62691',NULL,NULL,unistr('GALI ROHITH KUMAR\u000aEmail: gali.rohith63@gmail.com | Phone: +91 83176 62691 | Location: Hyderabad, India\u000aProfessional Summary\u000aCity Operations Manager with experience managing multi-outlet operations, team\u000aleadership, and process improvement. Expertise in recruitment, payroll, inventory control,\u000avendor coordination, last-mile operations, and digital platform management including\u000aSwiggy, Zomato, and Urban Piper. Adept at SLA adherence, fleet management, data analysis,\u000aand business process optimization. Skilled in documenting workflows, generating MIS\u000areports, collaborating with stakeholders for business requirements, and leading 50-60\u000amember teams to deliver efficiency and customer satisfaction.\u000aCore Competencies\u000a• City & Multi-Outlet Operations\u000a• Team Leadership & Performance Management\u000a• Recruitment & Training\u000a• Payroll & HR Compliance\u000a• Inventory Control & Vendor Negotiation\u000a• Customer Experience & Escalation Management\u000a• Digital Platform Management (Swiggy, Zomato, Urban Piper)\u000a• Data Analytics & MIS Reporting\u000a• Business Requirements Gathering & Documentation\u000a• Process Mapping & SOP Development\u000a• P&L Management & Cost Control\u000a• Strategic Planning & SLA Management\u000a• Last-Mile Operations\u000a• Fleet & Vendor Coordination\u000aProfessional Experience\u000aCity Operations Manager\u000aLAMROK, Hyderabad | Mar 2023 – Apr 2025\u000a• Directed city-level operations across multiple outlets, ensuring adherence to SOPs\u000aand service quality\u000a• Managed recruitment, training, and payroll\u000a• Coordinated operations on Swiggy, Zomato, and Urban Piper for online order\u000amanagement and fulfilment\u000a• Handled customer escalations and optimized workflows to improve satisfaction\u000a\u000a• Performed operational data analysis to identify process bottlenecks and recommend\u000aimprovements\u000a• Collaborated with stakeholders to gather and document business requirements for\u000aprocess enhancements and digital integrations\u000a• Developed MIS reports and dashboards to track performance indicators for decision-\u000amaking\u000a• Documented and improved operational processes and standard operating\u000aprocedures\u000a• Oversaw vendor procurement, inventory control, supply planning, and fleet\u000aperformance\u000aCity Operations Manager\u000aVSK Services, Hyderabad | Mar 2021 – Feb 2023\u000a• Led city-wide operations for multiple locations, managing a team of 50+ staff\u000amembers\u000a• Supervised workforce scheduling, recruitment, and training programs\u000a• Administered payroll, HR documentation, and compliance\u000a• Managed vendor relationships and digital platform (Swiggy, Zomato, Urban Piper)\u000alistings and updates\u000a• Resolved customer issues via escalation management and ensured operational\u000astandards\u000a• Coordinated inventory, procurement, and negotiations\u000a• Generated and maintained regular reports to monitor performance and highlight\u000aimprovement opportunities\u000aEducation\u000aB. Tech, St. Mary’s Engineering College | 2015 – 2019\u000aIntermediate (MPC), Sri Chaitanya Jr. College | 2013 – 2015\u000aSSC, Mother Teresa High School | 2013\u000aAdditional Details\u000a• Languages: English, Telugu, Hindi\u000a• Availability: Immediate\u000a• Willing to Relocate: Yes'),NULL);
INSERT INTO candidates VALUES(835,9,NULL,'GAURAV TIWARI','gauravtiwari5557@gmail.com','73',NULL,NULL,'GAURAV TIWARI is an Operations, Maintenance Excellence & Digital Transformation leader with 11+ years of experience in manufacturing strategy and large-scale program management. He has proven expertise in Lean, Six Sigma, and AI/ML-driven predictive analytics, with a strong background in strategic planning, project execution, and supporting top leadership.','pending','row_19','2025-11-20 11:53:50','2025-11-25 11:00:55','+91-7763807031',NULL,NULL,unistr('GAURAV TIWARI\u000aOperations Excellence | Manufacturing Strategy | Digital\u000aTransformation\u000a+91-7763807031 gauravtiwari5557@gmail.com www.linkedin.com/in/gauravtiwari26\u000aSUMMARY\u000aOperations, Maintenance Excellence & Digital Transformation leader with 11+\u000ayears in manufacturing strategy, Industry 4.0 enablement, and large-scale\u000aprogram management. Proven expertise in Lean, TPM, Six Sigma, SAP PM, and\u000apredictive analytics, delivering measurable impact on OEE, throughput, and cost\u000areduction. Skilled in building business cases, presentations for top leadership,\u000acustomer engagement, advisory to leadership and benefit-tracking models.\u000aExperienced in multi-workstream program orchestration with cross-functional\u000ateams, vendors, and ecosystem partners. Passionate about consulting,\u000ainnovation, and capability building on the shop floor.\u000aEXPERIENCE (TATA STEEL LIMITED)\u000aSenior Manager, Maintenance and Operations, Hot\u000aStrip Mill\u000a03/2023 - 10/2024 Jamshedpur\u000aDirected a ₹125 Cr capital project for HSM utility system, collaborating with\u000aEngineering & Projects team.\u000aLed a 150+ member team across operations & maintenance, vendor\u000amanagement, and contractors.\u000aDelivered ₹5 Cr annual savings by redesigning vendor contract strategy and\u000acompetitive bidding.\u000aSpearheaded energy optimization projects, improving cooling tower efficiency\u000aand reducing utility costs.\u000aAchieved divisional recognition for TQM best practices and led process audits\u000aacross multiple units.\u000aConducted a feasibility study for capacity enhancement of the utility section to\u000asustain 4 million tons of annual production.\u000aExecuted Green Belt projects to maximize equipment availability by 20% and to\u000areduce water consumption costs by 2.2 crores.\u000aImplemented AI/ML-driven predictive analytics program, reducing downtime\u000aand enhancing reliability; established scalable framework aligned with Industry\u000a4.0 roadmap.\u000aIntroduced an online work permit system, a digital transformation initiative to\u000areduce job cycle time and enhance worker''s safety.\u000aMaintenance Manager, Cold Rolling Mill\u000a04/2020 - 02/2023 Jamshedpur, IN\u000aReduced downtime by 37% through an e-Maintenance app and digitized\u000aworkflows.\u000aSpearheaded a SAP PM rollout to enable ERP interoperability across\u000adepartments.\u000aReduced downtime in CGL, delivering 64,000 tons of production gain and\u000asignificant cost savings.\u000aStandardized excellence practices across Tata Steel’s global operations by\u000adriving Process Improvement Team (PIT) initiatives.\u000aWorked across PLTCM and CGL lines and achieved the best equipment\u000aavailability.\u000aExecutive Assistant to COMM\u000a12/2016 - 03/2019 Jamshedpur, IN\u000aSupported VP in strategy design, annual planning, and ₹900 Cr budget\u000aoversight for maintenance operations.\u000aCoordinated monthly CXO review meetings, aligning 25 departments on KPIs,\u000acost, and asset performance.\u000aIntroduced common inventory concepts, helped in reducing inventory by 3.7\u000acrores.\u000aLed formulation of Annual Business Plan for FY’18 and FY’19 having Asset\u000aManagement, Cost Sustenance, Safety & Environment, New Technology &\u000aDigitisation roadmap.\u000aIntroduced multi-Skilling and helper-less models, reducing contractor\u000aworkforce by ~700+ while improving productivity.\u000aEDUCATION AND\u000aCERTIFICATIONS\u000aB. Tech in Mechanical Engineering\u000aBirla Institute of Technology, Mesra\u000a06/2009 - 04/2013\u000aProject Management\u000aGoogle\u000a02/2025\u000aGreen Belt Six Sigma Certification\u000aTata Steel TQM\u000a02/2022\u000aSAP PM /SAP MM Practitioner\u000aSNTI, Tata Steel\u000a2020\u000aAWARDS & ACHIEVEMENTS\u000aAwarded by CEO & MD, Mr. T V Narendran for\u000aBest project in ‘Theory of Constraints’.\u000aCompleted outdoor leadership and team-building\u000aexpedition with Madam Bachendri Pal and\u000acompleted a trek to reach the summit of Siyari\u000atop at 11862 ft\u000aAchieved the 2nd prize in Kaizen across Tata\u000aSteel Limited India and SEA\u000aSelected for CXO-level strategy conference at\u000aMacau for long-term roadmap planning.\u000aSKILLS\u000aDigital Transformation SAP PM\u000aBusiness Case Development\u000aFinancial Modelling\u000aStakeholder Management\u000aProject Management Industry 4.0\u000aPredictive Maintenance Operations\u000aMaintenance Supply Chain Management\u000aIOT Lean TQM AI/ML for reliability\u000aBenefit Tracking Business Development\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000aE  q\u000a\u000aEXPERIENCE (TATA STEEL LIMITED)\u000aManager Maintenance, Blast Furnace\u000a07/2014 - 11/2016 Jamshedpur, IN\u000aAchieved 98.3% asset availability and 92% OEE, setting a performance\u000abenchmark.\u000aImproved MTBS from 45 → 67 days and reduced MTTR by 30%.\u000aRestructured shop floor team and optimized the team-size from 12 to 7\u000anumbers by centralizing the resources and eliminating responsibility overlap.\u000aReduced MTTR (Mean Time to Repair) critical equipment from 82 hrs to 57 hrs\u000a(Completed with TOC methodology).\u000aInitiated cost reduction measures, including competitive bidding,\u000aindigenization of imported spares.\u000aManager Trainee Technical\u000a07/2013 - 06/2014 Jamshedpur, IN\u000aImproved the efficiency of new compactor at Wire Rod Mill from 91.7% to\u000a98.3%\u000aIncreased rolling speed, resulting in a 17% throughput increase at New Bar Mill\u000aMAJOR PROJECTS\u000aE- Maintenance App\u000aDigital Transformation Project:\u000aSpearheaded a digitalization initiative to monitor\u000athe health of 500+ actuators using response-time\u000aanalytics, reducing unplanned downtime by 37%.\u000aLed a cross-functional team of 3 (IT &\u000aInstrumentation) to design and deploy predictive\u000amaintenance workflows.\u000aCreated a business case and ROI model,\u000ashowcasing the direct impact on asset reliability,\u000aOEE improvement, and EBITDA contribution.\u000aPredictive Maintenance of rotating\u000aequipment\u000aAI/ML enabled project:\u000aLed cross-functional initiative with Central\u000aMaintenance, Electrical, and IT teams to implement\u000aan AI/ML-driven predictive maintenance model for\u000afurnace exhaust fans and other critical equipment.\u000aAchieved 30%+ ROI within the first year,\u000ademonstrating strong financial justification.\u000aPrevented two major breakdowns of furnace\u000aexhaust systems, safeguarding production\u000acontinuity and reducing potential downtime costs.\u000aReduction of Operational and\u000aMaintenance cost of Utility Systems\u000aIndigenizing imported material:\u000aIndigenized imported spare parts (previously\u000asourced from Europe) by developing in-house\u000adesigns using reverse engineering.\u000aIdentified and partnered with domestic\u000amanufacturers capable of producing high-quality\u000aspares at global standards.\u000aAchieved >70% reduction in spare part costs and\u000a12% overall Utility cost savings; created scalable\u000asourcing model contributing to EBITDA\u000aimprovement and footprint optimization.\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•\u000a•'),NULL);
