t and Catering Technology\u000aOriental School of Hotel Management, Wayanad, Kerala | 2006\u000a All India Senior Secondary School Certificate (Humanities)\u000aKendriya Vidyalaya IIT Powai, Mumbai, Maharashtra | 2003\u000aTRAINING & CERTIFICATIONS\u000aIndustrial Training – Hospitality Management\u000aTaj Varkala Beach Resort, Varkala, Trivandrum, Kerala | Oct 2004 – Mar 2005\u000a Gained hands-on experience in front office operations, food & beverage service, food production, and housekeeping.\u000a Shadowed senior team members to acquire in-depth operational knowledge of hospitality management.\u000a Adapted quickly to new skills, processes, and industry standards, enhancing overall performance.\u000aKEY PROJECTS AND ACHIEVEMENTS\u000a Optimized Recruitment & Onboarding Process – Successfully streamlined the hiring process at Cloud Partner Technologies,\u000areducing time-to-hire by 30% through improved ATS implementation and proactive talent pipeline management.\u000a Enhanced Employee Retention & Engagement – Spearheaded employee engagement programs, resulting in a 15%\u000aimprovement in retention rates by introducing structured performance appraisals, mentorship programs, and employee\u000adevelopment initiatives.\u000a Implemented HR Compliance Framework – Developed and enforced HR policies and compliance protocols, ensuring 100%\u000aadherence to local labor laws and regulatory standards.\u000a Business Growth & Client Acquisition – As a Business Associate, played a key role in expanding customer base by 20%,\u000atargeting high-potential clients and optimizing customer engagement strategies.\u000a Administrative & Process Efficiency – Led an initiative to digitize HR & administrative records, improving documentation\u000aaccuracy and reducing manual workload by 40%.\u000a Successful Coordination of Large-Scale Training Programs – Designed and conducted employee training workshops,\u000aenhancing workforce skills and productivity across multiple departments.\u000a Cost Optimization in HR Operations – Identified cost-saving opportunities in payroll, benefits, and administrative expenses,\u000aresulting in a 12% reduction in HR operational costs.\u000a Strategic Workforce Planning – Developed a workforce planning strategy aligning with business growth, ensuring optimal\u000astaffing levels and skill availability.'),NULL);
