onducted market research of U.S. healthcare industry for developing go-to-market and product strategies.\u000aFRANKLIN TEMPLETON – Hyderabad\u000aCompliance Business Analyst August 2020 – June 2023\u000a• Monitored compliance for 120+ EMEA funds of $80B+ AUM, ensuring adherence to investment policies and\u000apreventing trade-execution violations across portfolios.\u000a• Facilitated 10+ IPO clearances and 5+ fund launches, enabling timely go-live through prompt regulatory\u000areviews and coordination with fund managers.\u000a• Streamlined Bloomberg-based workflows saving 300+ analyst hours through rule-based automation process.\u000a• Developed ESG screening mechanisms across 30+ funds, ensuring alignment with sustainability mandates\u000aand evolving EU regulatory frameworks.\u000a• Detected and escalated a $15M erroneous trade in real time, preventing trading error and a financial penalty.\u000aSUMMER INTERNSHIP\u000aLandmark Group – Bengaluru\u000aRetail Strategy and Operations April 2024 – May 2024\u000a• Developed a store ranking model using NPS and sales data to identify performance gaps across 20+ stores,\u000aenabling targeted actions that improved in-store customer experience and operations.\u000a• Benchmarked 5 competitor’s product mix and pricing, to improve SKU availability and average sales per day.\u000aEDUCATION\u000aIndian Institute of Management (IIM), Kozhikode June 2023 – April 2025\u000aMaster of Business Administration (MBA)\u000aBhavan’s Vivekananda College, Hyderabad June 2017 – Sept 2020\u000aBachelor of Commerce (B.Com)\u000aADDITIONAL\u000aInternational Exposure: Attended IE Business School, Madrid (Course: Innovation and Digital Transformation)\u000aLanguages: Fluent in English, Telugu and Hindi; Conversational Proficiency in Tamil and Kannada\u000aTechnical: MS Office Suite, Jira, Zoho Projects, Bloomberg, Charles River, Lucidchart, SQL, Power BI'),NULL);
