 companies for target screening a French Engineering Services\u000aprovider, shortlisting ~12 key targets by analyzing offerings, performance metrics & market positioning\u000a• Provided strategic recommendations to client-side CXOs, assisted managing partner in initiating discussions\u000awith shortlisted targets for a ~€20 million acquisition, ensuring alignment with business objectives & priorities\u000aMBA SUMMER INTERN April - June 2022\u000aICRA Ltd. (A Moody’s-Affiliated Credit Rating Agency)\u000aGurugram, Haryana, India\u000aGrowth and Business Development\u000a• Contrived 2 client acquisition strategies, basis which developed a database to contact 100+ prospective clients;\u000aContacted 9 book running lead managers for IPOs, converting one for association with the firm.\u000a• Conducted comparative analysis of 7+ credit rating agencies using parameters like rating drift and volatility to\u000apublish in sales deck.\u000a\u000a.\u000aEDUCATION Indian Institute of Management, Indore\u000aMaster of Business Administration\u000a73.95% 2023\u000aIndian Institute of Management, Indore\u000aBachelor of Arts (Foundations in Management)\u000a72.65% 2021\u000aThe Shishukunj International School, Indore\u000aHigher Secondary Certificate\u000a90.20% 2018\u000aThe Shishukunj International School, Indore\u000aSenior Secondary Certificate\u000a95.00% 2016\u000aCERTIFICATIONS \u000a• Awarded Green Belt Certification in Lean and Six Sigma Practices by KPMG India (2021)\u000a• “Corporate Strategy”, University of London (2021) & “Foundations of Business Strategy”, University of Virginia\u000a(2020) via Coursera; Alteryx: Real-Life Exercises for Data Analytics (2024) via Udemy\u000aCO-CURRICULAR\u000aACHIEVEMENTS\u000a• National Semi-finalist, Diageo Bespirited; Achieved all-India rank 32 among 346 teams (Top 10 percentile) in\u000aBespirited Qualification Round (2022)\u000a• National Semi-finalist, L''Oréal Brandstorm (Top 8/12,900+) teams; Ideated a sustainable packaging method\u000ato reduce plastic waste generation (2022)\u000a• National Finalist, Strategia Business Case Study Competition, Shailesh J. Mehta School of Management,\u000aIndian Institute of Technology, Bombay (2020)\u000a• Winner, IIM Indore Cricket League (2021 & 2022) and IIM Indore Football League (2022)'),NULL);
INSERT INTO candidates VALUES(842,9,NULL,'Abhishek Nair','abhisheknair917@gmail.com','83',NULL,NULL,'Abhishek Nair is an experienced Business & Growth Analyst with approximately 3 years of experience, including two stints in Founder''s Office roles. He demonstrates strong analytical, operational, and strategic planning skills, with a proven track record in driving revenue growth, improving efficiency, and managing stakeholders.','pending','row_26','2025-11-20 11:53:50','2025-11-25 11:00:55','6281034240',NULL,NULL,unistr('6281034240 · abhisheknair917@gmail.com · linkedin.com/in/abhishek-nair917\u000aBengaluru, Karnataka\u000aAbhishek Nair\u000aBusiness & Growth Analyst, Kapiva Ayurveda\u000aDoctor Channel Lead\u000aSpearheaded revenue growth, elevating Doctors’ Channel contribution to 10% of D2C revenue while expanding team from 17 to 30\u000adoctors.\u000aLed strategic website/store interventions resulting in 80% surge in organic leads, driving a 15% rise in Order per Customer (OPC)\u000ametric.\u000aEnhanced operational efficiency through the implementation of data-driven strategic initiatives, achieving a customer retention rate\u000asurpassing the D2C metric by 20%.\u000aJan 2023 - Feb 2024\u000aP R O F E S S I O N A L E X P E R I E N C E\u000aFounder’s Office\u000aPlayed a pivotal role within the Analytics and core strategy team, championing a pilot initiative focused on elevating customer\u000aretention and enhancing the lifetime value of the Hero Product by 13%.\u000aImproved retention rate by 8 pp for higher AOV customers with multiple value added propositions aimed at customer adherence and\u000aawareness.\u000aOperations Intern, Thermopads Private Limited \u000aApril 2022 - June 2022\u000aK E Y S K I L L S\u000aProficient in MS- Excel, SQL(BigQuery, Metabase), Looker, Google Analytics, CleverTap, Mixpanel, WebEngage Analytics, Microsoft\u000aSuite.\u000aExperience in A/B Testing, Business Intelligence, Retention Revenue Planning, Stakeholder Management, Strategy Planning.\u000aC O - C U R R I C U L A R A C T I V I T I E S\u000aSocial Media and Content Head SpeakOut! (Mental Health Service).\u000aInternational Press Representative for MUN.\u000aAssociate Growth Manager, Jar \u000aMar 2024 - Mar 2025\u000aManual Buy Charter\u000aOwned daily revenue performance and RCA for One-Time Purchase charter; managed ultra high-intent user projects driving 35% of\u000adaily revenue.\u000aIncreased customer LTV by 10% DoD via curated checkout values and reward logic for high-net-worth users.\u000aLed homepage optimization with behavior-based personalization, boosting conversions by 10%.\u000aCustomized buy flow for high-churn users, driving 6% DoD revenue growth.\u000aAuthored PRD for upsell buy flow, increasing AOV by 20% among high-intent users.\u000aE D U C A T I O N\u000aManipal Institute of Technology\u000aBachelor of Technology (BTech), Electrical and Electronics Engineering.\u000aCGPA -8.04\u000aFounder’s Office, BrightCHAMPS \u000aApr 2025 - Present\u000aOwned and curated sales incentive policies across different business regions to drive revenue growth while controlling costs and\u000asustaining team motivation.\u000aContributed to mid-funnel metric stabilisation carefully collaborating with pre-sales/sales and tech.\u000aContributed to creation and delivery of investor MIS for performance tracking and strategic decision-making.\u000aEnhanced quarterly tutor hiring pipelines with a careful data driven approach.\u000aLed internal review audits for overall team efficiency and morale judgement.'),NULL);
INSERT INTO candidates VALUES(843,9,NULL,'CHRIS JACK WALTER','chrisjackwalter@gmail.com','58',NULL,NULL,'Chris Jack Walter is an experienced professional with a background in strategy consulting, product management, and founder roles, demonstrating strong analytical, communication, and operational skills in various business contexts.','pending','row_27','2025-11-20 11:53:50','2025-11-25 11:00:55','9345464260',NULL,NULL,unistr('CHRIS JACK WALTER\u000alinkedin/chris-jack-walter| chrisjackwalter@gmail.com | Ph: 9345464260\u000aEDUCATION\u000aIndian Institute of Management (IIM), Visakhapatnam Year\u000aMaster of Business Administration 2023\u000aLoyola College, Madras University, Chennai Year\u000aBachelor of Commerce, First Class with Distinction 2021\u000aWORK EXPERIENCE\u000aCARS24 – Vendor Price Optimization Strategy Gurgaon\u000aFounder’s Office June 2025 – Aug 2025\u000a Analyzed vendor pricing for API services, identified usage inefficiencies and pricing gaps driving cost optimization.\u000a Performed comparative benchmarking of vendor services & pricing to uncover cost saving levers and service gaps.\u000a Built a data driven pricing & usage models to provide leadership actionable insights for strategic decision making.\u000a Aligned business teams on the data driven pricing strategy and strengthened outcomes from vendor negotiations.\u000aMarket Expansion Strategy – Packaging Manufacturer Bangalore\u000aFreelance Strategy Consultant March 2025 – May 2025\u000a Advised a Gujarat based corrugated box manufacturer on a market expansion strategy for Karnataka, evaluated\u000athe operational requirements, local logistics, and financial viability of setting up a new production facility.\u000a Market research identified fragmented manufacturing hubs and machine downtime as challenges for direct entry.\u000a Created scalability framework with production volume for transition from outsourced manufacturing to in house.\u000a Mapped potential fulfilment hubs, suppliers and govt industrial clusters to prepare for future in house operations.\u000aBranded Water Can Startup (Pre-launch) Bangalore\u000aFounder Oct 2024 – Feb 2025\u000a Created business model leveraging branded water cans as advertising real estate, offering consumers discounted\u000awater while monetizing through ad partnerships, blending physical distribution with performance-led branding.\u000a Conducted customer segmentation and pricing analysis to identify adoption drivers and define customer persona.\u000a Designed sourcing, delivery, and acquisition strategy tailored for a low-margin, high-volume distribution model.\u000a Pitched to local brands and validating B2B monetization interest and the potential for recurring ad revenue.\u000aThe Digital Fifth Mumbai / Bangalore\u000aAssociate Consultant (Strategy Consulting / Product & Program Management) May 2023 – Oct 2024\u000a Drove the strategic pivot of India''s largest and Asia''s third-ranked financial news platform Moneycontrol with\u000a50M+ users into a fintech platform with Credit Bureau, Account Aggregator, Fixed Deposit and Lending products.\u000a Designed a comprehensive 3-year Go-To-Market strategy, emphasizing customer engagement which successfully\u000aguided product launches in achieving a significant increase in user acquisition across new and existing segments.\u000a Conducted industry analysis to pinpoint market positioning and growth opportunities, formulated a product\u000aroadmap that transitioned 1M+ users to fintech consumers by tapping into the emerging BFSI market trends.\u000a Implemented MIS and provided the CPO with insights using dashboards and weekly steering committee meetings.\u000a• Pioneered the creation of 2 products from concept to product launch, through the use of wireframes, and BRDs,\u000aleading to a 10X increase in daily user acquisition and a 4X increase in user engagement within the first 6 months.\u000a• Conducted competition analysis and benchmarked 20+ competitors for features addressing the market demands.\u000a Utilized Clevertap for A/B testing and analytics to increase user base by 2000% in 6 months of the product launch.\u000a Built 15+ proposals, led pre-sales strategy meetings, scoped requirements and aligned delivery expectations.\u000a Program managed Karnataka Banks projects driving the creation of governance structures, and project roadmaps.\u000a Managed daily business activities, oversaw performance metrics, identified process gaps, and reported to CPO.\u000a Developed phase wise plans, structured processes alongside department heads to streamline business activities.\u000a Oversaw work flow creation for schematic products focusing on Operational Flow, TAT, Internal Controls and MIS.\u000a Managed 5 cross-functional teams of 30+ members to launch products reducing development timeline by 20%.\u000a Established partnerships, employed agile methodologies, to reduce project lifecycle by 33%, and costs by 25%.\u000aMa Foi Strategic Consultants Chennai\u000aStrategy Intern (Growth & Operations Strategy) April 2022 – May 2022\u000a Involved in end-to-end strategy engagement for a flavoured milk processor, designed supply chain strategy using\u000amarket research, mapped logistics and conducted cost analysis to ascertain the feasibility of operations expansion.\u000a Identified multiple sourcing locations based on cost analysis in a 150 km radius in 3 districts, negotiated with\u000avarious stakeholders willing to supply raw materials on estimated variables, demand, time period and pricing.\u000a Conducted secondary research on the firm''s competence and proposed a three-pronged strategy for growth.\u000aADDITIONAL INFORMATION (SKILLS)\u000aAgile Project Management: Jira, Asana, Trello | UX/UI Design: Figma, Visily | User Analytics: Clevertap, Google Analytics'),NULL);
