aWorking in a simulated corporate environment.\u000aMentoring 5 juniors for business and management events.\u000aSKILLS\u000aCorporate Communication Content Writing\u000aMeta Ads Video Editing Leadership\u000aStrategic Thinking Strong Work Ethics Canva\u000aMS Word Marketing\u000aPERSONAL PROJECTS\u000aCo-Founder (Bobaa Daddyy) (07/2023 - Present)\u000aA Taiwanese delicacy (boba/bubble drinks) brand.\u000aWe started with putting up a pop-up store/stall in the biggest\u000afestive season in Kolkata (a city in the state of West Bengal, India).\u000aCurrently serving 8 flavours.\u000aSold over 6000 glasses within a year.\u000aThe Daddyy TV (Podcast) (03/2024 - Present)\u000aCo-host in a podcast called The Daddyy TV.\u000aThe vision of the podcast is to host the underdogs of any and every\u000aindustry while promoting a culture of relentless efforts and\u000adedication. Defying the social norm of defining success with\u000amonetary achievements and social status.\u000aLANGUAGES\u000aEnglish\u000aNative or Bilingual Proficiency\u000aHindi\u000aNative or Bilingual Proficiency\u000aINTERESTS\u000aEntreprenureship Finance Social Work\u000aInnovation Product Design NFT\u000aProduct Design Films and Film Making Writing\u000aReading Businesses\u000aCourses\u000aCourses\u000aAchievements/Tasks\u000aAchievements/Tasks\u000aAchievements/Tasks'),NULL);
INSERT INTO candidates VALUES(848,9,NULL,'Ashish Gyan','ashish.gyan@gmail.com','80',NULL,NULL,'Ashish Gyan is an entrepreneur and marketing leader with 14+ years of experience in brand strategy, D2C, and retail growth, demonstrating strong founder-level ownership and data-driven execution. He has a proven track record in scaling ventures, leading cross-functional teams, and a keen interest in Digital Marketing and AI.','pending','row_32','2025-11-20 11:53:50','2025-11-25 11:00:55','+91 7829525509',NULL,NULL,unistr('Core Skills\u000aWork Experience\u000aContact\u000aHyderabad | Jamshedpur\u000a+91 7829525509\u000aashish.gyan@gmail.com\u000aLinkedIn Profile\u000aCareer Snapshot\u000aBrand Strategy & Growth: Category Creation | GTM Leadership | Experiential Campaign Design.\u000aEntrepreneurial Leadership: 0→1 Business Building | Founder-Mindset Execution.\u000aInnovation & Scale: First-Principles Problem Solving | Process Design | Sustainable Growth\u000aSystems.\u000aMarketing Manager\u000aAlmond House, Hyderabad\u000aApril 2023 - November 2025\u000aAshish Gyan | Brand Strategy, Marketing & 3X Founder.\u000aEntrepreneur and marketing leader with 14+ years of experience\u000abuilding brands, scaling retail and D2C businesses, and driving omni-\u000achannel growth. Operate at the intersection of strategy, storytelling,\u000aand performance, combining data-driven execution with founder-level\u000aownership. Known for blending creativity with commercial discipline\u000ato turn ideas into sustainable, high-growth brands.\u000aKey Accomplishments\u000aLed brand strategy that secured Best Mithai Awards across Times of India, Zomato, and Swiggy\u000aGenerated ₹70 Crores ($7.89 Million) incremental revenue at Almond House, driving a 15%\u000aYoy growth.\u000aLed my coffee startup to a ₹5 Crores ($565,377) valuation from 15 lakhs in 2 years.\u000aMentored 3 startups in B2C, Beverages and Fashion sectors for GTM strategy.\u000aDriving growth for 14 premium outlets, delivering 10–25% YoY revenue increase through\u000aintegrated retail and digital strategy.\u000aScaled e-commerce and built Q-comm presence, building a unified omni-channel\u000aecosystem across store, web, app, and marketplace touchpoints.\u000aDesigned and executed CRM-led acquisition and retention frameworks, boosting repeat\u000apurchase and customer lifetime value.\u000aApplied first-principles understanding of Google Ads, Meta, and Amazon Ads to drive\u000aperformance-led growth and optimize ROI.\u000aLed cross-functional teams reimagining customer experience, visual storytelling, and\u000amerchandising, translating brand equity into conversion.\u000aDrove festive and gifting campaigns (Rakhi, Diwali), achieving 25% YoY growth on new\u000ainitiatives; owned marketing P&L and media ROI.\u000aBrand Consultant\u000aBridgegap Consultancy LLP, Hyderabad\u000aFebruary 2023 - April 2023\u000aBuilt brand strategy and identity for an idea-stage toys startup - Namasthe World\u000athrough deep market and consumer research.\u000aAuthored the brand guideline book, defining positioning, tone, and design system for\u000alaunch readiness.\u000aDeveloped the consultancy’s in-house content marketing strategy, strengthening\u000avisibility and inbound lead flow.\u000a\u000aEntrepreneurial Experience – D2C, Lifestyle & Agri Ventures\u000a2012 - 2022\u000aFounded and scaled ventures across D2C, lifestyle, and agri, combining brand building\u000awith digital-first growth.\u000aDrove e-commerce expansion via owned web, app, and marketplace ecosystems,\u000ausing first-principles mastery of Google Ads, Meta, and Amazon commerce.\u000aBuilt lean GTM strategies and performance funnels, improving conversion efficiency\u000aand acquisition cost.\u000aSet up an organic farm near Cuttack, testing sustainable models for farm-to-market\u000adistribution.\u000aLed multi-disciplinary teams across ops, design, and marketing; codified growth\u000asystems now embedded in later roles.\u000aFreelance & Projects, Content Strategy\u000a2015 - 2021\u000aDelivered content and growth strategy for brands across men’s grooming, fintech,\u000ahospitality, and blockchain.\u000aProduced SEO, website, and social campaigns, driving measurable traffic, conversion, and\u000avisibility.\u000aDeveloped industry reports, brand profiles, and investor decks that strengthened\u000apositioning and market readiness.\u000aEducational Background\u000aLondon Metropolitan University, U.K., Class of 2012\u000aMS - Medical Genetics, Graduated with a 6.1 CGPA.\u000aB.Sc Biotechnology, Genetics, Chemistry, Bangalore University, Class of 2010\u000aGraduated with 78% (First Division), Head -Student committee 2008-2010.\u000a12th Grade, Vidya Bharathi Chinmaya Vidyalaya, Jamshedpur, Class of 2006\u000aGraduated with 76%, National-level Debate champion.\u000aSkills\u000aStrategic & Leadership\u000aAdditional Information\u000aComp.leted 2 full and 4\u000ahalf-marathons, 2014-\u000a2019\u000aU-15 National-level\u000aLawn Tennis Player\u000afor Bihar/Jharkhand,\u000a2000-2003.\u000aKeen interest in Books\u000aacross genres.\u000aBrand Positioning & Rebranding\u000aMarket Expansion & Go-to-Market Strategy\u000aCross-functional Team Management\u000aData-Driven Decision Making\u000aCertification/Short Courses\u000aGenerative AI Mastermind by Outskills\u000a360° Leadership Assessment (Internal)\u000aAwards & Recognitions\u000aAlmond House - Best Mithai, Times Food and Nightlife Award -\u000a2 years\u000aIndulge - Best Gelato, Times Food and Nightlife Awards - 2023\u000aAlmond House - Best in Mithai, Zomato Restaurant Awards, 3\u000ayears.'),NULL);
INSERT INTO candidates VALUES(849,9,NULL,'SHREYASHI SONI','Shreyashi.soni29@gmail.com','89',NULL,NULL,'Shreyashi Soni is an experienced AI Product Manager and Entrepreneur with 5.5 years of experience, demonstrating strong product ownership, strategic thinking, and execution excellence in scaling digital products and founding a profitable QSR brand. She possesses strong analytical and communication skills, with significant experience in AI and data-driven decision-making.','pending','row_33','2025-11-20 11:53:50','2025-11-25 11:00:55','+91 7974043986',NULL,NULL,unistr('SHREYASHI SONI\u000aAI Product Manager, Entrepreneur | NIT Bhopal | Ex: 5.5 Years\u000a+91 7974043986 | Shreyashi.soni29@gmail.com | linkedin.com/in/shreyashisoni/\u000aSummary\u000aI am a Product Manager and Entrepreneur with 5.5 years of experience driving large-scale products across\u000aEdTech, AgriTech, GovTech and F&B. Proven track record in end-to-end product ownership, stakeholder\u000amanagement, and building scalable solutions impacting over 30M+ users. Founder of a profitable QSR brand,\u000acombining strategic thinking, execution excellence, and customer-centric design.\u000aWork Experience\u000aFounder, JuJu Bowl\u000a10/2024 - Present\u000a• \u000aFounded a clean-eating Quick Service Restaurant brand in Lucknow; identified an ~INR 500 Mn\u000aunderserved market through user interviews & segmentation study\u000a• \u000aDrove a 56% cart-to-order rate (vs. 35% city avg.) by optimising pricing, digital marketing and deploying\u000atargeted oLers across channels; 20% average weekly customer growth with a 61.8% repeat user rate\u000a• \u000aOptimised operations to achieve <10 mins Turnaround Time for 100+ SKUs\u000aProduct Manager, Samagra\u000a07/2022 – 09/2024\u000aOdisha’s Agri-commerce platform, logistics dashboard and AI chatbot\u000a• \u000aLaunched Odisha’s first Agri-commerce platform, enabling 10M+ farmers with digital seed discovery,\u000apre booking, and payment capabilities, eliminating distribution delays and inventory shortages\u000a• \u000aIntegrated eRUPI cashless vouchers for aid distribution, eliminating payment delays & improving affordability\u000a• \u000aDeveloped a real-time logistics dashboard, enabling officials to track inventory & seed distribution\u000a• \u000aBuilt Ama Krushi AI, a RAG based LLM chatbot delivering personalized agricultural advisory to 8M farmers,\u000awith 100+ local data sources synthesized in vector DB\u000a• \u000aLed 0-1 product dev from concept to deployment, establishing scalable infrastructure for state-wide adoption\u000a• \u000aSecured CxO-level buy-in and led cross-functional teams to deliver full platform in 3 months, driving\u000aadoption of 19,000+ quintals of seeds booked by 10,000+ farmers within the first week\u000aBuilt and scaled Saral App to digitise and automate evaluation of physical school assessments in real time,\u000aeliminating manual eLort by 100x for teachers & enabling faster, standardised assessments\u000a• \u000aDesigned AI-based OCR workflows with structured validation, achieving 100% character recognition accuracy\u000a• \u000aApplied user feedback and analytics to optimise performance, improving adoption and reducing churn\u000a• \u000aLaunched statewide in Uttar Pradesh, powering assessments for 17M+ students across 139K schools\u000a• \u000aEnabled role-based monitoring dashboards with Google Analytics + telemetry, allowing oLicials to\u000amake real-time, data-driven decisions\u000a• \u000aExpanded adoption to Rajasthan, Assam, & Sikkim, reusing Saral’s building blocks for state assessments\u000aDesigned a case management system for the High Court of Kerala, targeted to reduce dispute resolution time\u000a• Reduced summons delivery time from 3 years to 4 months by designing automated escalation workflows\u000a• Led API integrations with 7+ external systems (NPCI, Police IT, etc), enabling seamless case processing\u000a• Delivered MVP in 90 days, securing pilot adoption by Kerala High Court in Kollam\u000a• Architected a scalable SaaS platform with modular deployments & integration-ready design\u000a\u000aFinishing Manager, Larsen & Toubro\u000a07/2018 – 10/2020\u000a• Delivered design and construction-ready drawings for Salsette27, a $90Mn project, by leading a 3-member team\u000a• Led the finishing delivery of Bombay Dyeing ICC, a 58-floor tower, ensuring a zero-defect turnkey handover\u000a• Managed design, material sourcing, client coordination & BOQs, balancing quality & cost across projects\u000aCertifications\u000aIBM Certified AI Product Manager IBM Specialisation in Generative AI for Product Managers\u000aOutskill’s AI Accelerator Program Outskill’s Generative AI Mastermind Program\u000aStrengths\u000aFirst Principles Problem Solving and Innovation Stakeholder Alignment & Cross Functional Leadership\u000aCustomer Centric Product Development Product Roadmap and GTM Strategy\u000aData Driven Decision Making Agile Execution, Experimentation and Delivery\u000aTechnical Skills\u000a• Product & Project Management Tools: Jira, Notion, Confluence\u000a• User and Market Research\u000a• Data & Analytics: SQL, Excel, Google Analytics, Tableau, MixPanel\u000a• Design & Prototyping: Figma, Miro, Adobe, AI Tools/Apps\u000a• Methodologies: Agile, Scrum, A/B Testing\u000a• Technical Knowledge: APIs & Integrations, Basic HTML/CSS, GitHub, System Architecture\u000a• Documentation and KPIs: Slack, MS Office Suite, Google Workspace\u000aEducation\u000a2020 - 2022: Master''s in Management Studies (Urban Management) | CGPA 3.9/5\u000aCEPT University, Ahmedabad, Gujrat\u000a2013 - 2018: Bachelor of Architecture | CGPA 8.15/10\u000aNIT Bhopal, Madhya Pradesh\u000aKey Achievements\u000aSuccessful Product Launches: Delivered multiple digital products adopted by state govts & enterprise clients,\u000aincluding Saral, an EdTech app scaled to 17M+ students and Odisha’s AgriTech platform used by 10M+ farmers\u000aEntrepreneurship: Founded JuJu Bowl, a profitable clean-eating QSR brand in Lucknow, with a 61% repeat user rate\u000aLeadership & Execution: Mobilised and led a 60-member team to digitise 100,000+ polling booths across\u000aMadhya Pradesh for the Election Commission, generating INR 4.5 Million Profit in 3 months\u000aImpact Consulting: Conducted Impact evaluation of NABARD’s Wadi Project, strengthening program delivery'),NULL);
INSERT INTO candidates VALUES(850,9,NULL,'MALLELA DEVAKI NANDHA PAVAN KUMAR','Pavanmallela555@gmail.com','70',NULL,NULL,'An MBA student specializing in Finance and Marketing with 18 months of experience in finance operations, accounting, and brand management. Possesses strong analytical and communication skills, with expertise in financial analysis, cost management, digital marketing, SAP, Tally, and Microsoft Office.','pending','row_34','2025-11-20 11:53:50','2025-11-25 11:00:55','9491736755',NULL,NULL,unistr('MALLELA DEVAKI NANDHA PAVAN KUMAR\u000a9491736755 Pavanmallela555@gmail.com\u000aProfile Summary\u000aI am an MBA student specializing in Finance and Marketing, with a solid foundation in financial analysis, cost\u000amanagement, and digital marketing strategy. I bring 18 months of combined experience across finance\u000aoperations, accounting, and brand management roles. My background includes preparing financial reports,\u000aoptimizing cost structures, and executing marketing campaigns that enhance brand visibility. Skilled in SAP (FI-\u000aCO), Tally, and Microsoft Office, along with hands-on expertise in Google Ads, SEO optimization, and social\u000amedia management. I combine analytical and creative strengths to drive both business growth and financial\u000aefficiency, delivering data-driven results in dynamic environments.\u000aAcademic Qualifications\u000aDegree Year Institute, University/ Board %/CGPA\u000aMBA 2025 Paari School Of Business, SRM University AP 7.50\u000aDEGREE B.COM 2023 Bhavanms Degree College 61.3\u000aMPC 2019 Sri Chaitanya Junior College 7.23\u000aSSC 2017 Sasi Em High School 8.8\u000aProfessional Experience {18 Months}\u000aFINANCE EXECUTIVE – 04/2022 – 07/2023 (RAJAHMUNDRY)\u000aSatyanarayana & Co., CMA Firm, Rajahmundry\u000aWorked as a Finance Executive in a CMA (Cost Management Accounting) firm, managing finance operations,\u000aauditing, and cost analysis.\u000a• Prepared and analyzed financial reports to support budgeting and cost control.\u000a• Monitored expenses, performed reconciliations, and assisted in financial forecasting.\u000a• Conducted stock audits for client firms, including Sri Venkateswara Agencies, verifying, and reconciling\u000aphysical inventory with accounting records to ensure accuracy and compliance.\u000a• Supported audit documentation, cost optimization, and process improvements during a 15-month tenure.\u000aAssociate Feb 2025 – Apr 2025\u000aLabsity,\u000a• Worked on client interaction and coordination tasks, supporting day-to-day business operations.\u000a• Assisted in handling email communication and back-end follow-ups for project progress.\u000a• Supported digital marketing and documentation efforts as needed.\u000a• Developed communication and organizational skills while collaborating with cross-functional teams.\u000aTotal Professional Experience: 18 months (15 months in Finance roles + 3 months in\u000aMarketing/Operations)\u000a\u000aProfessional Courses\u000aCompleted CMA Foundation\u000a• Developed foundational knowledge in cost management and accounting principles.\u000a• Acquired skills in tracking expenses, budgeting, and conducting financial analysis.\u000a• Learned strategies for cost control and improving financial performance.\u000aInternship project\u000aHindustan Unilever Limited, Rajahmundry, Andhra Pradesh\u000aFinance Intern (May 2024 – June 2024)\u000a➢ Assisted with SAP data entry, navigation, and process optimization.\u000ao Streamlined data management and reporting processes in SAP by accurately entering\u000afinancial data and optimizing workflows, enhancing overall data accuracy and operational\u000aefficiency for the finance department.\u000a➢ Conducted tax verification and managed challan payments.\u000a➢ Verified tax records and managed challan payments, ensuring compliance with statutory regulations\u000aand timely submission of financial documents, minimizing discrepancies and potential audit risks.\u000a➢ Coordinated entry permits and ensured smooth departmental operations.\u000a➢ Supported asset verification and contributed to supply chain efficiency.\u000aCourses & Certifications\u000a• SAP Finance & Controlling (FI-CO) Power User Course\u000a• Microsoft Office Intermediate Program (Word/Excel/PowerPoint)\u000a• e-Filing training on Filing of E-PAN, Income Tax, GST, TDS, Registration of ESIC, EPFO and DSC, Tally.\u000aPositions And Responsibilities\u000a• Organized the "HR ODESSY" event at the Ameya Business Fest, Paari School of Business, SRM\u000aUniversity AP Event Coordinator\u000a• I participated in the Samaj Seva course at SRM University as part of the MBA curriculum, focusing on\u000acommunity service projects. Contributed to food distribution and blanket distribution drives to\u000asupport social welfare initiatives.\u000aSkills & Expertise\u000aI have knowledge of financial analysis, cost management, auditing, and reporting, with familiarity in SAP (FI-\u000aCO), Tally, and Microsoft Office. I also have basic skills in digital marketing, including SEO, social media\u000amanagement, Google Ads, and website content optimization. I am good at communication, teamwork, client\u000acoordination, event planning, and campaign execution. These skills help me contribute effectively to business\u000aoperations and growth.'),NULL);
INSERT INTO candidates VALUES(851,9,NULL,'Hemaswitha Nunna','Swithanunna11@gmail.com','77',NULL,NULL,'MBA Gold Medalist with 1.5 years of experience in GTM strategy, deals advisory, and market research for startups. Possesses strong expertise in structuring business problems and executing go-to-market initiatives.','pending','row_35','2025-11-20 11:53:50','2025-11-25 11:00:55','+91-9059835772',NULL,NULL,unistr('StartSmart (Venture by WishWorks & Mirai Ventures) – Strategy & Ops Associate, Founder’s Office jun ’25 - present\u000aWishWorks Solutions (via Mirai Ventures) – Market Research & GTM Analyst | Jan’25 – Jun’25\u000aPiramal Foundation | Gandhi Fellow | Rayagada and Nabarangpur, Odisha Jun ’21 - Apr ‘23\u000ajan’24 - july ‘24Aadhya Airtek – Business Development & Strategy Intern\u000aHemaswitha Nunna\u000aSwithanunna11@gmail.com| +91-9059835772 | linkedin.com/in/hemaswitha -nunna\u000aMBA Gold Medalist with 1.5 years of experience in GTM strategy, deals advisory, and market research for startups and ventures.\u000aDeveloped strong expertise in structuring business problems, executing go-to-market initiatives, and driving measurable outcomes.\u000aNow seeking high-impact opportunities to apply strategic thinking and GTM expertise in advisory roles.\u000aWORK EXPERIENCE\u000a• Co-led end-to-end GTM strategy from website launch to deal closure, converting 6 deals (~3% of total outreach, ~15% of\u000ainterested leads) including accelerator program clients and 3 international startups (USA & Africa).\u000a• Executed targeted outreach campaigns to 200 new clients, generating 80 interested leads and moving 40 to final negotiations,\u000aimproving deal pipeline visibility.\u000a• Conducted market research, competitive benchmarking, and opportunity-risk analysis, delivering actionable insights for GTM\u000astrategy and business growth.\u000a• Streamlined workflows using Asana, Basecamp, and Notion, reducing campaign execution time from 17 days to 7 days, enhancing team productivity\u000aand cross-functional collaboration.\u000a• Managed founder-level communications and LinkedIn presence, strengthening stakeholder relationships and external visibility.\u000a• Developed pitch decks, proposals, NDAs, and agreements, enabling structured client interactions and smooth deal execution.\u000a•\u000a• Led market research and advisory for Bosch’s Evoco product, identifying 7 potential domains beyond automotive; top 3 domains\u000ashortlisted for strategic implementation.\u000a• Designed GTM and fundraising recommendations, ~60% implemented to improve product positioning, market entry, and\u000aexpansion strategy.\u000a• Built dashboards and optimized reporting workflows, accelerating decision-making and improving team efficiency by ~50%.\u000a• Directed cross-functional research initiatives as project lead, supporting founder decisions and enabling evidence-based strategy\u000aexecution.\u000a• Represented the company as stall manager at ELASIA and PIA industry events, driving brand visibility and client engagement.\u000a• Secured ₹13 lakhs in investment and generated ₹8 lakhs in sales, contributing to revenue growth and business expansion.\u000a• Developed strategic sales pipelines and managed relationships with 3rd-party vendors, optimizing operations and partner\u000acoordination.\u000a• Assisted in product strategy and business initiatives, supporting market positioning and competitive differentiation.\u000aEDUCATION\u000aAdarsh Institute of Management & IT, Bengaluru\u000aMBA | 2022 – 2024 | GPA: 8.53/10 | Gold Medalist (Top 1%)\u000aSri Padmavathi Women’s Degree College, Tirupati\u000aBSc | 2019 – 2022 | GPA: 9.1/10 | Gold Medalist (Top 1%)\u000aSKILLS\u000a• Strategy & Advisory: GTM Strategy, Deals Strategy, Market Research, Competitive Analysis, Business Analysis, Value Creation, Risk & Opportunity\u000aAssessment\u000a• Analytical Tools: Excel (Advanced), PowerPoint, Google Sheets, Notion, Asana, Basecamp\u000a• Marketing & Outreach: Email Campaigns, LinkedIn Management\u000a• Frameworks & Analysis: SWOT, PESTEL, Benchmarking, Market Trends, Opportunity Evaluation'),NULL);
INSERT INTO candidates VALUES(852,9,NULL,'Ali Abdul Salam','ali.abdulsek@gmail.com','94',NULL,NULL,'Ali Abdul Salam is an experienced Business Operations & Analytics professional with a Master''s in Business Analytics & AI. He has a strong background in data analysis, operational excellence, and strategic planning, with experience as a Co-Founder of an AI-driven startup.','pending','row_36','2025-11-20 11:53:50','2025-11-25 11:00:55','+91 9744022907',NULL,NULL,unistr('Ali Abdul Salam\u000aBusiness Operations & Business Analytics | Reporting & Compliance\u000aali.abdulsek@gmail.com| +91 9744022907\u000aBusiness Analyst Intern\u000aThya Technologies – Thuwal, Saudi Arabia\u000aFeb 2023 – Aug 2023\u000aDocumented and optimized internal workflows, improving team efficiency by 40% through process redesign.\u000aDeveloped performance reports and KPI dashboards to monitor operational performance and support decision-\u000amaking.\u000aAssisted with data validation, reconciliation, and reporting accuracy checks.\u000aSupported market and competitor research, providing actionable insights for strategic planning,\u000aExperience\u000aBusiness Operations & Reporting Analyst (Graduate Role – Contract)\u000aSmart Advanced - Jeddah, Saudi Arabia\u000aAug 2024 – May 2025\u000aPromoted from intern to contract for delivering process and reporting solutions that enhanced reliability across finance,\u000asales, and operations.\u000aDesigned and deployed 8+ interactive dashboards (Power BI & Excel) to monitor operations, sales, and financial KPIs,\u000aimproving decision-making by 25%.\u000aAutomated recurring reporting workflows using SQL queries and Excel macros, reducing reporting turnaround time by\u000a30%.\u000aConducted variance analysis and forecasting, improving reporting accuracy from 85% to 97%.\u000aCoordinated with finance, sales, and IT teams to resolve data discrepancies and align reporting with business priorities.\u000aDocumented standard operating procedures (SOPs) for reporting and operational workflows, increasing team efficiency\u000aby 20%.\u000aMonitored inventory and operational tracking, identifying bottlenecks and ensuring timely resolution.\u000aLinkdln| | Bangalore\u000aAI Intern (Student Role)\u000aMetamaze – Thuwal, Saudi Arabia\u000aJan 2024– April 2024\u000aContributed to the training of AI and NLP models by performing large-scale data annotation and labeling across text\u000aand image datasets (20K+ samples).\u000aConducted data validation and quality audits, improving dataset accuracy from ~88% to 97% through structured review\u000aloops.\u000aCollaborated with AI engineers to optimize training data pipelines, reducing labeling inconsistencies and improving\u000amodel precision by 12%.\u000aStandardized dataset documentation and tagging frameworks, enabling 30% faster data ingestion during model\u000aretraining cycles.\u000aData Analytics Intern - WISER Program KAUST Smart\u000aKAUST – Thuwal, Saudi Arabia\u000aJuly 2022 – August 2022\u000aLed data analytics and visualization for the WISER initiative in partnership with KAUST Smart, driving insights into\u000asmart housing performance and sustainability.\u000aAnalyzed 20,000+ data points on energy usage, operational efficiency, and financial metrics from KAUST’s smart\u000ahousing systems.\u000aDeveloped interactive dashboards and automated reports (Power BI & Excel) to track energy efficiency, consumption\u000atrends, and budget utilization.\u000aDelivered data-driven insights that identified 15% potential energy savings and informed cost-optimization strategies for\u000athe campus housing network.\u000aCoFounder\u000aMirsal – KAUST, Saudi Arabia\u000aNov 2024 - Jan 2025\u000aFounded Mirsal, an AI-driven driver scoring and risk detection startup, after winning the Saudi Youth Sustainability\u000aHackathon (1st Place out of 200+ teams).\u000aDesigned and validated the business model and financial projections (3-year ROI: 28%), aligning with sustainability and\u000aautomotive safety objectives.\u000aConducted market validation with 5+ industry stakeholders and refined product feasibility through cost–benefit analysis\u000aand user testing.\u000aSecured partnership interest from Ceer Motors after delivering a financial and technical pitch showcasing 40% potential\u000areduction in accident-related costs.\u000aEducation:\u000aMaster in Business Analytics & Artificial Intelligence\u000aVlerick Business School – Leuven, Belgium | Jul 2024\u000aAdvanced coursework in Data Strategy, Data Governance Principles, Business Simulation, and Python for Analytics.\u000aConsulting projects: Reporting automation, KPI development, financial impact analysis, AI-powered decision-making.\u000aBachelor in Business Administration & Aviation Management\u000aISBR – Bangalore, India | 2022\u000aFocus on corporate finance, operations, and analytics. Graduated with distinction (79%)\u000a\u000aProjects:\u000aCustomer Churn Prediction (Python) - Telenet:\u000aApplied predictive modelling with a financial impact analysis to guide retention strategy.\u000aApplied SMOTE for class balancing and improved prediction accuracy.\u000aBuilt predictive models integrating financial impact analysis on customer retention strategies.\u000aFinancial and Sales Dashboard (Power BI): Coloryt:\u000aDesigned dashboard with KPIs, profitability metrics, and variance analysis, improving data visibility and decision-\u000amaking.\u000aBuilt custom metrics using DAX and implemented interactive filters.\u000aVlerick ICP Project(Team Project):\u000aCreated NLP-powered ETL pipeline to analyze faculty evaluations, linking findings to budget allocation and compliance\u000areporting.\u000aCreated a Python-based ETL pipeline to clean and analyze 3 years of SET data.\u000aIdentified gender and nationality bias using statistical tests (Mann-Whitney U, Kruskal-Wallis).\u000aSeedPay Financial Analysis (VC Project) – Stride Ventures\u000aConducted a financial diagnostic and performance review for SeedPay, a fintech startup, on behalf of a venture capital\u000aclient.\u000aAnalyzed cash flow, burn rate, and customer acquisition metrics to identify underlying profitability and liquidity\u000achallenges.\u000aBuilt KPI dashboards and valuation models to visualize financial health and guide investment recommendations.\u000aOperational Analytics Dashboard (Power BI & SQL) – Johns Hopkins Aramco Healthcare (JHAH)\u000aAnalyzed health record and operational data to identify workflow inefficiencies across departments.\u000aDeveloped interactive dashboards tracking patient flow, appointment utilization, and staff productivity.\u000aProvided data-driven recommendations that improved operational visibility by 30% and reduced report turnaround time\u000aby 40%.\u000aRevenue Forecasting & Performance Optimization (Python & Power BI) – Smart Advanced\u000aDeveloped a forecasting model using Python and time-series analysis (ARIMA) to predict monthly sales and operational\u000aperformance.\u000aIntegrated model outputs into a Power BI dashboard, allowing management to visualize trends and compare forecasts\u000aagainst actuals.\u000aIdentified seasonal demand patterns and pricing inefficiencies, leading to a 10% improvement in forecast accuracy and\u000amore efficient inventory planning.\u000aSkills:\u000aOperations & Compliance: Customs entry knowledge, SOP documentation, workflow optimization, order/backlog\u000amanagement, compliance reporting\u000aData & Reporting: SQL queries, Excel (PivotTables, VLOOKUP, macros), Power BI dashboards, variance analysis, data\u000areconciliation\u000aCoordination & Communication: Cross-functional teamwork, stakeholder engagement, client reporting, issue escalation\u000aTools & Systems: MS Excel, Power BI, SQL, Python (basic), ERP familiarity\u000aLanguages:\u000aEnglish - Fluent\u000aMalayalam - Fluent\u000aArabic - Intermediate\u000aFrench - Beginner\u000aLeadership & Extracurricular Activities:\u000aDiversity Ambassador – Vlerick Business School (2024): Represented the international student community, driving\u000ainitiatives that promoted inclusion, cultural awareness, and student engagement.\u000aStudent Body Representative – ISBR Business School (2021–2022): Served as liaison between faculty and 200+\u000astudents, coordinating academic and welfare programs to enhance student experience.\u000aStudent Representative – KAUST Schools (Grade 11 & 12): Elected to lead student council initiatives, organizing\u000aevents and strengthening communication between students and administration.\u000aModel United Nations (MUN) Delegate (4 years): Participated in multiple regional conferences; recognized for\u000adiplomacy, public speaking, and policy drafting.\u000aAthletics & Team Leadership (U14–U19):\u000aCaptain of Football and Volleyball Teams; led squads to multiple inter-school and regional tournaments, fostering\u000ateamwork and discipline.\u000aCompeted in basketball, badminton, dodgeball, and ultimate frisbee at regional and MENA levels.\u000aSaudi Dodgeball Champion (2023) and MENA Ultimate Frisbee Competitor (2022).\u000aFinance & Investment Clubs – Vlerick & ISBR: Contributed to portfolio simulations, valuation analyses, and\u000ainvestment discussions; organized peer-led workshops on market strategy and personal finance.'),NULL);
