te May 2022 - Jun 2024\u000a• Collaborated directly with founders to design and execute growth initiatives, enhancing client engagement across a 100K+\u000aexpert network and driving a 12% uplift in conversion rates.\u000a• Led the launch of two products - one achieving $1M ARR within 12 months and another contributing 10%+ of monthly\u000arevenue within the first quarter.\u000a• Negotiated and executed a strategic vendor partnership that delivered 15% cost savings and reduced service turnaround time\u000afrom 24 hours to under 2 hours.\u000a• Partnered with marketing and sales teams implementing GTM strategies that improved client acquisition efficiency by 18%\u000aacross target segments.\u000a• Managed key accounts, identifying upselling and cross-selling opportunities that led to a ~15% increase in client wallet share.\u000a• Won the Arbolus India Shark Tank among seven teams, earning CEO sponsorship to commercialize a new business concept\u000awith $150K+ projected annual revenue potential.\u000aBETTER MORTGAGE India\u000aSenior Analyst Jul 2020 - May 2022\u000a• Audited property appraisal reports with 99.5% accuracy, identifying revenue leakages and supporting sales enablement.\u000a• Led a process transformation initiative that streamlined investor compliance, delivering $16K in monthly cost savings and\u000aimproving turnaround time by 25%.\u000a• Organized training for 5 new hire batches, strengthening process knowledge and adherence to GSE and investor guidelines.\u000aGOLDMAN SACHS India\u000aAnalyst Apr 2019 - Jun 2020\u000a• Collaborated with global relationship managers to onboard and service 150+ institutional and private wealth clients monthly,\u000aensuring seamless integration into GS systems and maintaining high satisfaction levels.\u000a• Partnered with cross-functional teams across five global offices to streamline client communication and delivery processes,\u000aimproving turnaround efficiency by 20%.\u000a• Automated client notification and reporting processes, cutting manual effort by 20% and increasing delivery accuracy for\u000ahigh-value accounts.\u000aEY GLOBAL DELIVERY SERVICES India\u000aAdvanced Associate Aug 2017 - Mar 2019\u000a• Executed multiple audit engagements under EY Global methodology, consistently recognized as a top performer for\u000adelivering high-quality, accurate results.\u000a• Collaborated with Canadian engagement teams to prepare audit workpapers, ensuring compliance with global standards.\u000aADDITIONAL INFORMATION\u000a• Spearheaded NUS MBA team to 2nd place at the MBA Olympics, driving performance and collaboration in the cohort.\u000a• Organized social and cultural events at Arbolus Technologies, managing logistics and budgeting for 50+ team members.'),NULL);
INSERT INTO candidates VALUES(856,9,NULL,'MUDIT GARG','mudit.garg24@bimtech.ac.in','80',NULL,NULL,'Experienced professional with a background in CEO''s office roles, strategic initiatives, digital transformation, and AI implementation, demonstrating strong analytical and communication skills.','pending','row_40','2025-11-20 11:53:50','2025-11-25 11:00:55','+91-6378176559',NULL,NULL,unistr('PROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE\u000aBajaj Allianz General Insurance\u000aCompany, Pune (India) \u000aAssistant Manager Jun 2024 – Present\u000aRole Summary: Working in the CEO’s Office at Bajaj Allianz, leading strategic initiatives to enhance customer experience through\u000adigital transformation, change management, process optimization, automation & product development. Partnering with\u000amultiple teams and leveraging industry insights & data-driven strategies to shape business strategy & explore growth opportunities\u000aStrategic Planning & Market Intelligence (CEO’s Office)\u000aGTM strategy\u000a& Market\u000aAnalysis\u000a Contributed to launch of HERizon care, India’s first women-centric health insurance plan, leveraging\u000amarket research insights to address key gaps & customer pain points\u000a Enhanced My Health Care Plan (MHCP) by analyzing global insurance trends, strengthening policy\u000acoverage, & driving competitive differentiation\u000a Assisted in Long-Range Strategy (LRS) & Annual Operating Plan (AOP) discussions by delivering research-\u000adriven insights to inform strategic business decisions\u000aCustomer\u000aExperience\u000a(CX)\u000a Partnered with Product & Design teams to run multiple A/B experiments aimed to optimize customer\u000ajourneys across all business lines (Health, Motor, Travel, Home & Cyber Insurance)\u000a Increased funnel conversion by 20% through benchmarking UX/UI performance, identifying key gaps, &\u000aspearheading implementation of targeted improvements\u000a Streamlined Online reputation management (ORM) workflows by identifying inefficiencies & introducing\u000aautomation via Generative AI\u000a Led end-to-end evaluation & onboarding of a third-party AI vendor, driving system integration &\u000asuccessful deployment, which enhanced response efficiency & customer satisfaction\u000a Automated social media responses, reducing turnaround time (TAT) & cutting operational costs by 14%\u000aChange\u000aManagement\u000a Revamped vehicle inspection workflows for two-wheelers (2W) & four-wheelers (4W), leveraging industry\u000abest practices to eliminate inefficiencies & accelerate digital transformation for faster assessments\u000a Increased automated KYC rate by implementing OCR based KYC flow with auto-population of user info\u000a Partnered with multiple teams, including ops, sales, product, legal & compliance, to ensure seamless execution\u000aCustomer Centricity (CEO’s Office)\u000aCustomer\u000aExperience\u000a Achieved 50% reduction in customer tickets (2.2L → 1.1L) through redesign of ‘Do Not Call’ (DNC) opt-\u000aout process through integration of automated workflows\u000aOnline\u000aPayments\u000aOptimization\u000a Partnered with IT to design a real-time payment monitoring dashboard to detect 1,000+ cases of\u000asuccessful payments without receipt generation/policy issuance.\u000a Conducted root cause analysis (RCA) & addressed process gaps, leading to 80% drop in payment failures\u000aSkills \u000aBusiness strategy, A/B testing, CRM, Change management, Strategic planning, Competitive benchmarking,\u000aStakeholder management, Digital marketing, Performance marketing, Product marketing\u000aTools \u000aGoogle Analytics, Meta Business Suite, Google Ads, Branch.io, Google Search Console, JIRA, Mixpanel, SQL,\u000aZapier\u000aElectricPe, Bengaluru Product Marketing Specialist (Summer Intern) Apr 2023 - Jun 2023\u000aDigital\u000aMarketing &\u000aGrowth\u000aInitiatives\u000a Implemented & optimized digital ad campaigns, driving increased app installations & sign-ups for\u000aElectricPe’s EV charging network of 10,000+ charging points\u000a Leveraged SEO/ASO strategies to improve website ranking and visibility, resulting in a 25% increase in\u000aorganic search traffic\u000a Executed performance marketing strategies, achieved 15% increase in conversion rates, reducing CAC\u000aBrand Building\u000a& Community\u000aEngagement\u000a Developed go-to-market (GTM) strategies for ElectricPe’s multi-brand EV store, driving high-intent leads\u000afor test drives & store visits\u000a Employed data-driven approaches to analyze customer behavior and campaign metrics, leading to a 10%\u000aboost in user engagement and a 12% decrease in bounce rates\u000a Managed & scaled social media presence, leading to a 40% increase in followers & stronger brand recall\u000a Led & scaled ‘Club ElectricPe’, a community for 150K+ EV enthusiasts to promote sustainable mobility,\u000aindustry engagement and strengthening ElectricPe’s positioning in the EV ecosystem\u000aAnand Road Lines, Ajmer Assistant Manager (Logistics) Nov 2021 – Jun 2022\u000a Managed B2B and B2C operations of fleet of 35+ heavy load vehicles across 4 states\u000a Deployed collaborative backhauling on multiple routes to improve profit margins by 12% & detention cost by 25%\u000a Partnered with multiple companies including Wonder cement, Reliance Industries (RIL) for their logistics requirements\u000a Collaborated with a client to create dock design modification to enable 3X space utilization, reducing detention costs\u000a Introduced an incentive-based model for drivers, improving operational efficiency and ensuring adherence to safety compliance\u000a Collaborated with technology teams to introduce automated invoicing & e-POD (Proof of Delivery) systems, reducing\u000abilling errors and accelerating payment cycles\u000a Designed standardized SOPs for fleet maintenance & driver management, reducing vehicle downtime & optimizing productivity\u000a Established digitization pathway for business through GPS based data capturing & analytics\u000aMUDIT GARG\u000aLINKEDIN- MUDIT_GARG\u000a mudit.garg24@bimtech.ac.in\u000a:+91-6378176559\u000a\u000aENTREPRENEURIAL STINT\u000aUnder1000 Store, Ajmer Nov 2020 – Nov 2021\u000aEntrepreneurial\u000aExperience\u000a Launched an E-commerce Men’s Fashion store in Ethnic wear segment targeting middle age value- buyers\u000a Managed listing and content strategy for products on Instagram & WhatsApp Business\u000aEDUCATION\u000aYear Qualification Institute Board/University\u000a2024 \u000aPGDM (MBA) – Marketing\u000awith IT/ITES\u000aBirla Institute of Management Technology\u000a(BIMTECH), Greater Noida \u000aAICTE\u000a2021 Bachelors (Arts) \u000aSamrat Prithvi Raj Chouhan Government\u000aCollege, Ajmer\u000aMaharshi Dayanand Saraswati\u000aUniversity, Ajmer\u000a2018 12\u000ath \u000aSamrat Public Sr Sec School, Ajmer CBSE\u000a2016 10\u000ath \u000aMaheshwari Public School, Ajmer CBSE\u000aCERTIFICATIONS\u000aDigital Marketing Fundamentals Diploma In Marketing Research\u000aGoogle Analytics Basics of Project Management'),NULL);
INSERT INTO candidates VALUES(857,9,NULL,'Soham Patil','psoham53@gmail.com','85',NULL,NULL,'Soham Patil is a Program Manager with 5 years of experience in Founder''s Office roles, adept at driving strategic and operational initiatives, process optimization, and cross-functional execution across healthtech and agritech. He demonstrates strong analytical acumen, data-driven decision-making, and a passion for AI.','pending','row_41','2025-11-20 11:53:50','2025-11-25 11:00:55','9558396663',NULL,NULL,unistr('August 2025 - Present\u000aApril 2024 - July 2025\u000aOctober 2022 - March 2024\u000aSoham Patil\u000aBusiness & Strategy Head : Founder’s office\u000aMumbai & Vadodara\u000a9558396663, 9016558446 | psoham53@gmail.com\u000aObjective\u000aProgram Manager with 5 years of experience driving customer experience, process optimization, and\u000across-functional execution across healthtech, agritech, and consumer platforms. Skilled in identifying\u000afunnel inefficiencies, improving retention, and creating scalable solutions that enhance user journeys.\u000aExperience\u000aLords Mark Agritech AI (Dozee - Lords Group), Mumbai\u000aHead of Business & Strategy : Founder’s Office\u000aPromoted internally by the founder to lead strategic and operational expansion for the group’s\u000anew Agri-AI initiative, Lords Mark Organic.\u000aLead and drove end-to-end business operations, ensuring seamless execution of strategic\u000ainitiatives and support the founders in strategic projects.\u000aRan multiple business experiments to identify new revenue streams and optimize existing ones,\u000aincluding NPDs launch, Subscription pricing model, Annual contracts etc.\u000aSpearheaded the GTM strategy for 1.2cr ARR B2B exotic vegetables & rental orchid business in\u000a8 months, ensuring recurring revenue to fund our AI initiatives.\u000aAchieved 40% logistics cost reduction and 30% cultivation cost optimization in 6 months.\u000aDirected field operations, product development, supply chain, sales, logistics, and ad-hoc\u000astrategic initiatives. Managed vendor relationships, contract negotiations, and procurement.\u000aDozee Health AI (Dozee - Lords Group), Bangalore\u000aProgram manager - Founder’s office\u000aSupport the Founders to execute key projects and manage the end-to-end execution of the\u000asame.\u000aIncreased hospital product adoption by 24%, driving direct revenue growth.\u000aReduced customer escalation tickets by 32% through performance improvements and feature\u000aadditions.\u000aLed end-to-end HubSpot implementation, achieving 89% adoption within 3 months.\u000aPlan and review projects & processes, analyze any red flags and organize interventions to keep\u000athings on track.\u000aCollaborated with cross-functional teams for execution of high-priority projects, crisis\u000amanagement, and firefighting.\u000aHandled business ad hoc duties or tasks delegated by the management to ensure smooth\u000aoperations and support their productivity.\u000aLeap Finance and Leap Scholar, Bangalore\u000aManager | Business Operations & Program management\u000aImproved student admit rate by 26%, resulting in ₹25 Cr incremental revenue.\u000aLed 4 central operations teams, driving efficiency and executing ad-hoc strategic projects.\u000aAuthored BRDs for product requirements; owned tech ticket lifecycle including UAT.\u000aOrganized events for students & university delegates (2,100+ students converted)\u000aCollaborated closely with stakeholders at all levels, including senior leadership, customers, and\u000avendors, to define and execute program/project.\u000aMonitored program/category performance metrics, analysed data, and provided\u000acomprehensive reports to track progress, identify trends, and make data-driven decisions.\u000aEnhanced user engagement by optimizing communication funnels across WhatsApp and other\u000aplatforms.\u000a\u000aMarch 2022 - September 2022\u000aJuly 2021 - Feb 2022\u000aFeb 2021 - July 2021\u000aJuly 2020 - Oct 2020\u000a2016 - 2020\u000aLeap Finance and Leap Scholar, Bangalore\u000aSenior Customer Experience & Ops Associate\u000aReported to Chief of Staff; conducted RCAs and insights reporting to improve business\u000aprocesses.\u000aImproved product experience by preparing detailed analysis reports for product team\u000aConducted detailed RCAs on business processes and funnels, and prepared insight reports for\u000athe Chief of Staff, enabling data-driven decision-making by management.\u000aLed weekly cross-functional meetings, acting as the customer voice to drive process\u000aimprovements that enhanced customer experience and retention.\u000aServed as SME for the Customer Experience & Ops team, conducting quality checks and\u000amentoring agents through regular 1:1 sessions.\u000aLeap Finance and Leap Scholar, Bangalore\u000aCustomer Experience & Ops Associate\u000aCollaborated with internal team members to resolve customer concerns and deliver enhanced\u000auser experience.\u000aUtilised telephone, online chat and email platforms to deliver outstanding customer service.\u000aAddressed customer inquiries, concerns and complaints by providing solutions and alternatives\u000aand followed up to confirm resolution.\u000aBYJU''S - The Learning App, Bangalore\u000aPre Sales Associate\u000aScaled Aakash-BYJU’s product funnel from lead prospecting to conversions.\u000aConducted product demos and presentations to boost adoption.\u000aBYJU''S - The Learning App, Bangalore\u000aBusiness Development Executive\u000aManaged K12 sales funnel from cold calling to closures.\u000aDelivered consistent conversions by driving customer-centric sales strategies.\u000aEducation\u000aGujarat Technological University, Ahmedabad\u000aBachelor of Engineering (Electrical Engg)\u000a9.13 CGPA\u000aSkills\u000aStakeholder Management\u000aCross functional collaboration\u000aProject & Program management\u000aProcess design & optimisation\u000aProblem solving & Critical thinking\u000aLanguages\u000aEnglish\u000aGujarati\u000aHindi\u000aMarathi\u000aTechnical Skills\u000aGoogle Sheets & Microsoft Excel | SQL | CRM Systems (HubSpot, ZOHO, Leadsquared)\u000aDashboard & Reports Creation | Funnel Optimization | Market Research & AI Tools'),NULL);
INSERT INTO candidates VALUES(858,9,NULL,'SHAKTI RANJAN NAIK','x23shaktir@iima.ac.in','84',NULL,NULL,'Shakti Ranjan Naik is an IITM-IIMA graduate and strategy professional with over 7 years of multinational experience in renewable energy and water infrastructure. He demonstrates strong expertise in strategic planning, business development, data analysis, and project execution, with a keen interest in AI.','pending','row_42','2025-11-20 11:53:50','2025-11-25 11:00:55','+91 9032568530',NULL,NULL,unistr('SHAKTI RANJAN NAIK\u000a+91 9032568530 | x23shaktir@iima.ac.in | www.linkedin.com/in/shaktirn\u000aIITM-IIMA graduate and strategy professional with 7.5+ years of multinational business experience in Renewable Energy and\u000aWater Infrastructure across the Middle East, Africa, and India. Proven expertise in Strategy, CXO Collaboration, Client-Facing\u000aBusiness Development and Proposals, Go-To-Market Strategy, Procurement, Consulting, and Digital Transformation.\u000aPROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE\u000aKEC International, RPG Group Gurgaon, India\u000aSenior Manager | Business Development, Sales and Tendering May 2024 – Present\u000aStrategy, Business Development, and Proposals manager for Renewables SBU. Reporting to Executive Director and VP - Proposals.\u000a• Internal Awards and Accolades: Selected in Future Leaders Board (1/10) and RPG Group Management Resource (1/30).\u000a• Strategic Road mapping & Growth strategy: Spearheading 0-to-1 growth initiative for a $100M Wind energy portfolio and\u000aBESS through strategic planning, defining differentiated go-to-market playbook, and value-based pricing.\u000a• Market Sizing & Segmentation: Conducted in-depth TAM/SAM/SOM analysis for India’s wind market for Turnkey EPC\u000aplayers and identified high-growth pockets with >15% CAGR across states.\u000a• Cross-Functional GTM Playbook and Long-Term Strategy: Developed a scalable GTM framework for Renewables SBU by\u000abundling products, policy, commercial and channel strategy; reducing time-to-market and increasing market penetration.\u000a• Client-Facing Business Development: Engaged with national regulators (MNRE, CEA, CII), IPPs (ReNew, Serentica, Gentari,\u000aABREN, Brightnight, BlueLeaf, Juniper, ACME, Powerica, KPE) & energy technology providers (Siemens Gamesa, Envision, Inox,\u000aGoldee) with goal to be the choice EPC.\u000a• Strategic Partnerships: Led multiple strategic partnerships and exclusivity agreements with IPPs, leading OEMs, and\u000aspecial subcontractors across Solar, Wind, and Green Hydrogen, contributing to increase in business opportunities.\u000a• Revenue Planning: Formulated a $300M revenue strategy and financial models for Solar, Wind, BESS, and Green Hydrogen\u000athrough market research, vendor consultations, policy analysis, and interviews with 10+ industry leaders.\u000a• Market Analysis & Competitive Intelligence: Conducted market and competitor analysis, providing insights to a develop a\u000aunique business model in Wind Energy, increasing market penetration, and refining the company’s value proposition.\u000a• Proposals: Secured $150 M Solar projects with leading PSU and currently managing a $500M pipeline of opportunities in\u000aSolar, Wind, and Green Hydrogen, driving significant growth in the renewable energy portfolio.\u000a• Thought Leadership & Industry Engagement: Youngest member of National CII Renewable Energy committee,\u000acomprising 15+ CXOs, and proposed innovative solutions and draft policies to solve ground issue for Renewable Energy EPC.\u000a• Cost Optimization and Process Improvement: Reduced cost estimates by ~5% through root cause analysis, competitor\u000abenchmarking, risk analysis, and developing a vendor evaluation and costing framework.\u000a• Strategy Toolkit: Applied strategic frameworks (Porter’s 5 Forces, SWOT, Risk Analysis, Ansoff, NTCP, Blue Ocean, Scenario\u000aPlanning) to craft differentiated positioning for Wind EPC, Green Hydrogen, and BESS in saturated solar markets.\u000aLarsen & Toubro (L&T) Limited, Construction Chennai, India\u000aSenior Engineer to Assistant Manager - II August 2017 – April 2023\u000aStrategy, Proposals, Procurement, and Business Development manager in Water International SBU for Middle East and Africa.\u000a• Strategy & Business Development: Developed a $1B go-to-market strategy and identified 5+ marquee developers for the\u000aEPC part of PPP projects in the Middle East while collaborating closely with senior leadership and C-suite executives.\u000a• GTM Strategy and CXO engagement: Secured CEO approval for market entry in East Africa for $100M+ prospects through\u000amarket and data analysis, PESTEL analysis, and market penetration strategies.\u000a• Proposals: Secured $ 900M worth Sewage and Industrial Effluent Recycling Plant (500 MLD+) while engaging with\u000agovernment & private clients for techno-commercial negotiations in UAE, Qatar, Oman, and Tanzania.\u000a• Team Leadership and Management: Attained a 35% success rate in international bidding by leading 30+ team members\u000aand compiled 350+ high-quality bid documents across 15+ international EPC and PPP proposals.\u000a• Procurement and Strategic Negotiations: Saved $3.8 million on $50M international procurement orders by leveraging\u000anegotiations, cost-benefit & total cost of ownership analysis, and strategic partnerships with 15+ international OEMs.\u000a• Project Operations and Data Analysis: Drove timely completion of a $200 Mn project and monitored profitability;\u000aReported to Vice-President and BU Head and built progress reports and dashboard for senior management.\u000aEDUCATION\u000aIndian Institute of Management – Ahmedabad | IIM-A 2023 – 2024\u000aMBA, Strategy and Finance – 3.311/4 | GMAT: 710, Q49 V38 IR 7 AWA 5.5\u000a• Leadership Positions: Vertical Head – PGPX Placement Committee; President – Consulting Club\u000aIndian Institute of Technology – Madras | IIT-M 2015 – 2017\u000aM.Tech, Construction Technology and Project Management – 8.8/10 | Rank 3/36\u000a• Published International Research Journal on Conveyor Performance.\u000aGITAM University, Visakhapatnam 2011 – 2015\u000aB.Tech, Mechanical Engineering – 8.8/10 | Rank 2/66\u000a• GATE Top 2%ile & L&T Build India Scholarship awardee (1/60 out of 20000+).\u000aADDITIONAL INFORMATION\u000a• Strategy Consulting: AI in BFSI - GTM Consulting Project for M/s Persistent | Circular economy digital product for M/s Notomia.\u000a• Sports: Represented Districts and University cricket teams (IIT, IIM, GITAM) | Selected as Intern Trek Leader in Indiahikes.'),NULL);
INSERT INTO candidates VALUES(859,9,NULL,'ROHIT MALIK','rohitmalik10594@gmail.com','48',NULL,NULL,'Rohit Malik is an experienced operations leader with over 3 years in high-growth startup environments, demonstrating strong capabilities in project management, data analysis, process improvement, and driving operational efficiency. He has a proven track record of scaling initiatives and collaborating with cross-functional teams.','pending','row_43','2025-11-20 11:53:50','2025-11-25 11:00:55','9561885736',NULL,NULL,unistr('EXPERIENCE\u000aSKILLS\u000aOperations Leadership\u000aCatalogue Management\u000aCategory Management\u000aVendor Management and Development\u000aMicrosoft Office\u000aLeadership and Team Management\u000aCost Management\u000aSchema Design and Data Modelling\u000aCreated and managed 4,000+ SKUs per city across grocery, pharma, home, sports, and fashion\u000acategories, achieving >90% coverage of standard barcoded products.\u000aDigitized catalogues for 100,000+ stores, improving discoverability and enhancing customer\u000aengagement by 30%.\u000aImplemented pricing and burn-threshold strategy across top SKUs, benchmarking against\u000acompetitor platforms, improving margin control and category profitability.\u000aAutomated catalogue creation by implementing a tech console with validations and\u000agovernance, trained teams, and improved enrichment coverage by ~18% with better taxonomy\u000aaccuracy.\u000aPartnered with brands and aggregators for new product integration (NPI), enabling faster\u000alaunches and richer assortment.\u000aReduced catalogue-related tickets by 90% through proactive monitoring, dashboard-driven\u000avalidations, and streamlined issue resolution.\u000aSpearheaded KPO/BPO processes for SKU sourcing and in-house catalogue creation,\u000astrengthening the company’s IP as a leading barcoded grocery repository.\u000aCollaborated with cross-functional teams (Category, Product, Engineering, Data Science,\u000aSales) to ensure seamless operations and timely project execution.\u000aPincode - (PhonePe Shopping App) - Central Team - Category + Catalogue\u000aFeb, 2023 - Present\u000arohitmalik10594@gmail.com || 9561885736 || www.linkedin.com/in/rohit-malik-600472150\u000aROHIT MALIK\u000aBuilt and scaled a micro-entrepreneur network of 5,000+ agents and 25 vendors across PAN\u000aIndia, improving campaign reach and operational efficiency.\u000aManaged end-to-end operations for fintech and digital projects, directly contributing ~45% of\u000amonthly revenue (₹35L+).\u000aPiloted and scaled new initiatives, including digital data entry and telecalling for KYC\u000averification, achieving 97% quality scores and ~60% net profitability.\u000aAutomated 3 high-volume workflows, enhancing efficiency and scalability across multiple\u000aprojects. Earned the recognition as the Top Performer in October and December 2021 for\u000acontributing to 80% of the company’s revenue for the quarter.\u000aImplemented quality control frameworks, reducing process errors and improving turnaround\u000atime by ~50%.\u000aSuccessfully transitioned multiple GigIndia projects into PhonePe systems while maintaining\u000aoperational continuity and client satisfaction.\u000aGigIndia (Acquired by PhonePe) - Operations Manager - Oct 2020 - Feb 2023\u000aScaled FOS (Feet on Street) sales operations, managing 5,000+ telecallers, 25+ vendors, and 16\u000acities; improved revenue by 8x and COGS by 4x.\u000aDesigned incentive and pay models, reducing attrition by 60% and increasing team\u000aproductivity.\u000aManaged multiple cross-functional teams (Sourcing, Quality, Accounts, Training, Micro-\u000aentrepreneurs) to ensure SLA adherence and client satisfaction.\u000aLed end-to-end execution for EdTech projects with 300+ educators, ensuring timely delivery\u000adespite changing client requirements.\u000aGigIndia - Operations Executive - Jan 2020 - Oct 2020\u000aEDUCATION\u000aAssortment and Pricing Strategy\u000aProficient in analyzing data\u000aChange Management\u000aProject Management\u000aE-commerce Operations\u000aSQL Basics\u000aData Enrichment and Quality assurance\u000aData Scraping and ETL Processed\u000a \u000aMIT School Of Management, Pune - MBA in General Management, 2017-2019\u000aBachelor Of Engineering (B.E,), 2012-2016'),NULL);
INSERT INTO candidates VALUES(860,9,NULL,'Kiran Vadapalli','kiranvadapalli9@gmail.com','76',NULL,NULL,'Senior Manager with 10 years of experience in driving business growth, team leadership, and operational excellence. Proven expertise in program management, Agile methodologies, and leveraging data-driven insights for strategic planning and project execution.','pending','row_44','2025-11-20 11:53:50','2025-11-25 11:00:55','+91 9700084677',NULL,NULL,unistr('Kiran Vadapalli +91 9700084677 | kiranvadapalli9@gmail.com | LinkedIn |\u000aSenior Manager - Client Servicing | Gurugram, India\u000aPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\u000aSenior Manager with 10 years of driving business growth and team leadership. Proven expertise in program management and Agile with\u000asuccess in delivering measurable business outcomes through data-driven insights.\u000aTECHNICAL SKILLS\u000aTools: Salesforce, Jira, Power BI\u000aMethodologies: Scrum Others: CRM Tools, Project Management Tools, Business Intelligence Tools, Agile, Hubspot, CSAT, SQL, Zoho,\u000aGoogle Studio/Analytics, Zendesk, Advanced Excel/Google sheets\u000aPROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE (10 Years)\u000aSenior Manager - Client Servicing Apr 2023 – Present, Gurugram, India\u000aGirnarsoft Software Pvt. Ltd – GetMyUni (Company providing innovative solutions in education technology)\u000a Led the integration of multiple teams and processes during the GetMyUni–CollegeDekho merger, centralizing operations to streamline\u000aworkflows, enhance communication through collaborative tools, and ensure seamless client delivery and product alignment across teams.\u000a Led and motivated a cross-functional team of 14 Customer Success Managers, Team Leads, Academic Counselors, and MIS Analysts to\u000adeliver an annual revenue increase of 14 Crore, effectively managing the product lifecycle using Agile methodologies.\u000a Conducted in-depth data analysis to identify inefficiencies and process improvement opportunities, leveraging data-driven insights to\u000aimplement improvements that boosted resource efficiency and performance.\u000a Led and managed a 20 high-budget campaigns with successful results in increasing ROI by 15%, conversion rates by 20%, and improving\u000acampaign profitability by 13% across 13 client accounts.\u000a Drove a Time-to-Task metric with 80 counselors to improve query resolution rates, resulting in a measurable improvement in conversion\u000ametrics.\u000aSenior Client Account Manager – Delivery (GetMyUni) Jun 2020 – Mar 2023, Bangalore, India\u000a Collaborated across teams (Client, Business Development, Content, Tech, Sales, Digital) to strategize and streamline lead generation\u000acampaigns using market analytics, competitor insights, and data-driven decision-making.\u000a Executed tasks in Scrum for product and tech teams, ensuring timely delivery and alignment with business goals.\u000aClient Account Manager – Operations (GetMyUni) Jun 2020 – Mar 2023, Bangalore, India\u000a Worked with PAN India clients to update SOPs for campaigns and metrics, improving operational workflows.\u000a Planned and executed month-on-month revenue strategies, enhancing leads optimization and structuring for profitability.\u000a Monitor Weekly & Monthly targets along with growth of sales qualified leads by driving outcomes from Pre-sales/Sales Team\u000aSenior Executive - Operations (R&R Salon Private Limited) Sep 2016 – Dec 2019, Bangalore, India\u000a(A company providing salon services with an evolving business model into e-commerce)\u000a Led growth strategies for the YLG India salon chain’s venture into e-commerce home salon services, successfully launching operations\u000aacross multiple cities.\u000a Managed a business vertical worth ₹7+ Cr, leading a team of 9 members and 80+ field staff, and executed GTM strategies by developing\u000aoperator/customer apps and order consoles to improve operational efficiency.\u000aIT Executive - Operations (StridesIT services Pvt Ltd.) Sep 2016 – Dec 2019, Bangalore, India\u000a Managed customer care operations for R&R Salon Private Limited, ensuring successful completion of day-to-day tasks and effective team\u000aperformance.\u000a Delivered seamless operational execution by overseeing client interactions and resolving escalations efficiently.\u000aPROJECTS\u000a Automated lead generation workflows for 170+accounts, boosting delivery revenue by 35% at GetMyUni.\u000a Boosted revenue 10% MoM & AOV 26% YoY through strategic bundling & wallet feature integration at YLG India.\u000aEducation:\u000aB.Tech in Electronics and Communication ( Jawaharlal Nehru Technological University (JNTUK-K) May 2015, Rajamahendravaram, India\u000aCERTIFICATIONS:\u000aFundamentals of Digital Marketing, Business Analytics, Project Management, Product Lifecycle Management\u000aACHIEVEMENTS: Received multiple Spot Awards from Getmyuni for improving CSAT and operational efficiency.\u000aLANGUAGES: English, Telugu, Hindi'),NULL);
INSERT INTO candidates VALUES(861,9,NULL,'Monarch Saha','saha.monarch2411@gmail.com','79',NULL,NULL,'Business and strategy professional with 2 years of experience in Founder''s Office, Project & Program Management, Marketing, and Business Analytics, demonstrating strong analytical acumen and leadership in cross-functional initiatives.','pending','row_45','2025-11-20 11:53:50','2025-11-25 11:00:55','+91-8249712469',NULL,NULL,unistr('WORK EXPERIENCE\u000aINTERNSHIPS\u000aACADEMIC PROJECTS\u000aSKILLS\u000aCERTIFICATIONS\u000aACHIEVEMENTS\u000aMonarch Saha\u000aEmail: saha.monarch2411@gmail.com; Phone: +91-8249712469; LinkedIn\u000aBusiness and strategy professional with 2 years of experience spanning Founder’s Office, Project & Program\u000aManagement, Marketing and Business Analytics, backed by an MBA (Technology) from IIT Jodhpur. Proven record of\u000aleading cross-functional initiatives that delivered patient acquisition growth, project delivery, campaign\u000aoptimization, and faster executive decision-making. Skilled in Agile project delivery, Stakeholder Management,\u000aTargeted Campaign Management and data-driven strategy execution to drive business impact and scale.\u000aMBA (Technology), Indian Institute of Technology, Jodhpur (7.87 CGPA) 2022-2024\u000aB.Tech. (CS & IT), Siksha O Anusandhan University (8.33 CGPA) 2017-2021\u000aSuraksha Diagnostics Ltd. | Marketing Manager May 2025 – Aug 2025\u000a● Spearheaded targeted digital and hyperlocal campaigns, achieving a 35% increase in impressions and 22% rise in patient\u000ainquiries within 60 days.\u000a● Designed a Performance Marketing dashboard (ROAS, CPA, CPL, CTR), reducing reporting cycles by 40% and enabling\u000afaster campaign optimization.\u000a● Orchestrated multi-channel acquisition campaigns with doctor engagement and outreach teams, improving\u000alead-to-patient conversions.\u000aMediversal Healthcare Pvt. Ltd. | Management Trainee – Founder’s Office June 2024 – May 2025\u000a● Directed the end-to-end rollout of a custom HRMS platform (payroll, appraisals, lifecycle management), cutting HR\u000aprocessing time by 30% and driving adoption among 200+ employees.\u000a● Collaborated with cross-functional stakeholders (HR, finance, operations, and tech teams) to define pain points, gather\u000afeedback, and prioritize features using MoSCoW and Kano models.\u000a● Utilized Agile methodologies and Jira for sprint planning, backlog grooming, and velocity tracking. Delivered key modules\u000awithin ensuring on-time delivery, and improving HR efficiency.\u000a● Performed Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) in Python (Pandas, Matplotlib) on 100k+ patient records from HIMS to identify\u000aseasonal admission trends, driving a 15% improvement in capacity planning.\u000a● Built Executive-level dashboards in Power BI, enabling real-time insights into hospital performance to help top\u000amanagement understand patient flow.\u000a● Developed a Pregnancy & Vaccination tracking system to monitor patient journeys, improving service personalization and\u000athereby increasing retention rates by 16%.\u000aCognizant | Programmer Analyst Trainee October 2021 – July 2022\u000a● Worked on contributing to software development and digital solutions delivery in a cross-functional technology team.\u000aSummer Internship | Mediversal Healthcare Pvt. Ltd. May. 2023 – July, 2023\u000a● Received a Pre-Placement Offer (PPO) for outstanding performance in leveraging analytics to drive strategic\u000adecision-making and delivering measurable impact on hospital operations and financial outcomes.\u000a● Learning and Development: Formulated effective and tailored training modules for different clinical departments.\u000aWinter Internship | Hamari Pahchan Dec, 2022\u000a● Highest fundraiser in the cohort; executed multiple campaigns, influencer outreach, awarded LOR & LOA.\u000a\\\u000a● Impact Of Various Health Indicators on Life Expectancy Prediction Using Linear Regression\u000a● Churn Prediction using Machine Learning Classifiers\u000aProgramming: Python, SQL, R\u000aTools & OS: Jupyter, R Studio, Microsoft Power BI, Jira\u000aData Visualisation: Empowering Business with effective insights (Tata & Forage)\u000aBusiness Analyst Experience Certification (Finlatics)\u000a“Runner Up” in Janhit Ideathon conducted by Jodhpur City Knowledge and Innovation Foundation & IIT Jodhpur\u000aEDUCATION'),NULL);
INSERT INTO candidates VALUES(862,9,NULL,'Ramu Mota','ramumotas@gmail.com','57',NULL,NULL,'Adaptable professional with a passion for innovation and entrepreneurship, skilled in data operations, project management, and developing AI/ML solutions. He has experience in managing data-driven projects and contributing to startup ecosystems.','pending','row_46','2025-11-20 11:53:50','2025-11-25 11:00:55','9014047019',NULL,NULL,unistr('Ramu Mota\u000aHyderabad | 9014047019 | ramumotas@gmail.com\u000aSummery\u000aAdaptable professional with a passion for Innovation and Entrepreneurship. Skilled in data operations,\u000aproject management and software development with experience in developing AI/ML solutions and\u000ainnovative digital products. Enthusiastic about contributing to projects that merge technology with\u000asustainable practices.\u000aExperience\u000aProject & Operations Associate\u000aTao Digital Solutions, Hyderabad (Dec 2022 – Feb 2025)\u000a● Production and Project Management: Managed data-driven AI/ML and GIS projects, ensuring\u000atimely delivery and quality adherence.\u000a● Stakeholder Management: Engaged with clients to clarify project requirements, ensuring\u000aalignment with quality and time metrics. Facilitated smooth communication between stakeholders\u000ato enhance project efficiency.\u000a● Mentorship: Assisted junior team members in the data annotation process, guiding them to\u000aimprove efficiency.\u000a● Innovation and Problem Solving: Conducted data annotation, Curations, and labeling to train\u000aAI and ML models. Monitored project progress, communicated updates, and ensured quality\u000aassurance. Supported pilot production and developed strategies for performance improvement.\u000a● Recruitment Process Involvement: Conducted interviews for potential candidates, and played a\u000akey role in the selection process by providing detailed feedback to HR.\u000aSoftware Developer Trainee\u000aRedIntegro, Bengaluru (May 2022 – Aug 2022)\u000a● Collaboration: Worked with the founding team to develop and deploy responsive websites,\u000asupporting the scaling of digital presence.\u000a● Rapid Development: Delivered projects on tight deadlines, adapting quickly to client needs and\u000afeedback.\u000aEducation\u000aKlr college of engineering and technology, B Tech (2017-2021)\u000aMajor: computer science and engineering\u000a● Gained strong technical skills in programming, data science, and IoT through coursework and\u000aworkshops.\u000a● Certified in Data Science and IoT with practical knowledge gained from industry-led programs.\u000aKrishnaveni jr college, Intermediate (2015-2017)\u000aMajor: Mathematics, Physics, Chemistry\u000a\u000aSkills & abilities\u000aProject Management: Overseeing project timelines, resources, and ensuring successful delivery along\u000awith quality assurance.\u000aInnovation Management: Applying creative problem-solving techniques to drive new solutions in\u000atech-driven environments.\u000aStartup Ecosystem Knowledge: Understanding of startup challenges, business growth strategies, and\u000afunding processes.\u000aTools & Technologies: Experience with AI/ML concepts, data analysis, and software development. AI\u000atools knowledge for workflow optimization and project efficiency.\u000aMentorship and Team Leadership: Experience in mentoring and fostering a collaborative work culture.\u000aProgramming: Familiarity with Python, SQL, JavaScript, HTML, CSS, Bootstrap.\u000aInterests\u000a● Exploring AI technologies and their applications in startup environments.\u000a● Professional networking, mentoring, and contributing to the startup ecosystem.\u000a● Passionate about innovation, entrepreneurship, and sustainable growth.'),NULL);
INSERT INTO candidates VALUES(863,9,NULL,'Vaibhav K','karemgarvaibhav@gmail.com','68',NULL,NULL,'Vaibhav K is a dedicated professional with 7 months of AWS DevOps and Linux experience, demonstrating strong technical skills in AWS services, networking, and scripting. He is eager to learn and possesses problem-solving abilities, making him a good fit for an AWS fresher role.','pending','row_47','2025-11-20 14:25:16','2025-11-25 11:00:55','+91 90673 73129',NULL,NULL,unistr('Vaibhav K\u000aDedicated professional with AWS, DevOps, and Linux expertise;\u000askilled in problem-solving, eager to contribute and grow\u000aprofessionally.\u000akaremgarvaibhav@gmail.com\u000a+91 90673 73129\u000aHyderabad, India\u000awo r k e x p e r i e n c e\u000aAWS DevOps Intern / Infoz IT - Hyderabad, India \u000aFeb – Sep 2024\u000aº Managed AWS infrastructure including EC2, RDS (MySQL/Aurora), DynamoDB, and S3.\u000aº Configured VPC, subnets, route tables, and ensured high availability. ‘\u000aº Handled Linux administration tasks: cron jobs, shell scripting for automation.\u000aº Secured AWS resources via IAM, NACLs, and S3 bucket policies.\u000aº Reduced system downtime by 20% by setting up proactive monitoring with CloudWatch and Prometheus\u000aS K I L L S\u000aº Cloud PlatformÊ\u000aº DevOps ToolÊ\u000aº Operating SystemÊ\u000aº ProgramminÁ\u000aº Version Contro×\u000aº Monitoring\u000aE d u cat i o n\u000aB-tech \u000a2018 - 2022\u000aElectronics and Communication Engineering At CMR Engineering College - India\u000aCGPA: 7.03\u000aC e rt i f i cat i o n s & Co u r s e s\u000aº AWS & DevOps - Teks Academy\u000aº Automotive Embedded Testing\u000aº AES Tech - Python Programming (in progress) - Udemy\u000a'),NULL);
INSERT INTO candidates VALUES(864,9,NULL,'Vaibhav','vaibhavkar0009@gmail.com','33',NULL,NULL,'Vaibhav has 3 years of experience in embedded verification and validation, with strong problem-solving and communication skills. However, the resume lacks proficiency in front-end web development technologies like HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and modern JavaScript frameworks, which are fundamental for this software developer role.','pending','row_48','2025-11-20 14:25:16','2025-11-25 11:00:55','+16125026038',NULL,NULL,unistr('Vaibhav\u000aMobile: +16125026038 | Email: vaibhavkar0009@gmail.com\u000aSummery:\u000aHaving 3 years of experience in Embedded Verification and Validation in Automotive Domain. Having strong\u000aunderstanding of verification and validation methodologies used in the industry and the Software Testing Life Cycle.\u000aHaving expertise in Continuous Integration/Continuous Delivery Pipeline with Jenkin Platform, AGILE Methodology,\u000aHIL Testing (VT System), ASPICE Methodology, Functional Safety, CANoe, CAPL, CAN, UDS and Test automation.\u000aProfile Summery:\u000a Having 3 years of experience in HIL implementation and validation, Automotive Real-Time\u000averification, and validation activities - majorly on ADAS and Body Electronics domain for\u000aAutonomous Vehicles.\u000a Possess good knowledge in ADAS, UDS, J1939, CAN, LIN and CANFD.\u000a Extensive experience in HIL benches such as VT Systems\u000a Proficient in VV tools like CANoe, CANape, CANoeDiVa, vTest Studio.\u000a Developed the RBS (Rest bus simulation) config file for Audi Inverter project to simulate the CAN bus.\u000a Extensive experience in configuration/Change management tools – Doors, GIT, JIRA.\u000a Good experience in handling SYS5 and SWE6 validation\u000a Expertise in CAPL scripting\u000a Good in\u000a Hands on experience in project execution compliant to ASPICE process model.\u000a Experience in Review of the test cases and test execution results and preparation of compliance matrix or\u000atraceability matrix.\u000a Good knowledge of ISO 26262 Functional Safety Standard.\u000a Excellent Knowledge of Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC), Software Testing Life Cycle (STLC)\u000aand Bug Life Cycle.\u000a Working Experience Functional Safety testing at Bench level.\u000a Good communication skills, established and maintained a productive working relationship with management\u000aand the team members.\u000aEducation :\u000a Bachelor of Technology in Electronics and Communication Engineering from CMR engineering College, JNTUH, 70%.\u000a Class XII from Sri Chaitanya Junior College, 92%.\u000a Class X from Pragna High School, 90%.\u000aSenior Test Engineer\u000a\u000aProjects:\u000aProject: ADAS feature Validation\u000aOrganization: Forvia (Hella) India Automotive Pvt Ltd\u000aRole: Senior Test Engineer\u000aResponsibilities:\u000a Analyze the System requirements and develop the corresponding System level test\u000a Performed Vehicle testing of Virtual Mirror ADAS features like Heater Module, Filed of View, Blind Spot Indication\u000aetc.\u000a Effectively engaged with clients, addressing inquiries, providing solutions and ensuring exceptional customer\u000asatisfaction through clear communication and a client-centered approach.\u000a Identifying the gaps, suggest solutions and lead enhancement to validation procedures, processes, and practices.\u000a Ensuring documents plus practices attain quality standards and applicable regulatory conformance.\u000a Complying with company guidelines and policies utilizing sound system validation practices.\u000a Ensuring the completeness and accuracy of system validation records.\u000a Accountable for the Manual and Automatic Testing, Requirement Review, TC Design, Scenario creation and execution in\u000aCANoe, VT Systems and vTest Studio.\u000a Involved in the Test Case designing for new projects in IBM Rational DOORS.\u000a HIL execution is in VT Systems.\u000a Defect Reporting and Tracking in JIRA\u000a Working on the automotive tools vTest, VT Systems, CANoe, CANalyzer, CAPL Scripting\u000a Handling the Change request management tool IBM Rational Change.\u000aProject: ADAS feature Validation\u000aOrganization: Forvia (Hella) India Automotive Pvt Ltd\u000aRole: Senior Test Engineer\u000aResponsibilities:\u000a Involving in the implementation of the CICD platform for ADAS Modules test execution\u000a Design Python libraries for Robot Framework to integrate external tools (CANoe, JIRA, DOORS, Jenkins)\u000a Report issues/bugs/Problem reports in JIRA\u000a CI / Jenkins Config preparation to invoke the CANoe for the test execution using python\u000a Fetching the reports from CANoe and integrating to Jenkins\u000a Support the test team for setting up the CI pipeline.\u000aProject: BCM Validation\u000aOrganization: Lear Automotive\u000aRole: Test Engineer\u000aBCM monitors and controls various electronic accessories in a Vehicle’s body. Typically, in a car the BCM controls the power\u000awindows, power mirrors, air conditioning, Immobilizer system, Central Locking, etc.\u000aResponsibilities:\u000a Understanding system requirement and converting to test Cases.\u000a Writing Test procedures for various testing features Like Locking, Diag, DTCs, Sleep Awake, Interior Lighting,Exterior\u000aLighting etc.\u000a Involved in Reviewing Test Procedures\u000a Execution of test cases using under Canoe and CANape Configuration environment\u000a Uploading all test results into IBM Doors\u000a Logging all the Defects found in current software into Jira\u000aProject: Diagnostics Validation\u000aOrganization: Lear Automotive\u000a\u000aRole: Test Engineer\u000a Implementing Diagnostics related test cases by using vTest Studio and CANoe\u000a Generating and executing DIVA test cases in CANoe environment and analysing the reports.\u000a Requirement analysis, creating test specifications and Test automation for\u000a different functionalities (Secure Variant Coding, Diagnostic Chrono stack) of ECU.\u000a Executing and Analysing test results and reporting bugs in JIRA.\u000a Responsible for DiVA test bench preparation and flashing related activities.\u000a Responsible for testing Diagnostics and Flash related tests in DTS Monaco\u000aCompetencies :\u000ao Working on Jenkins Pipeline with the help of Git, Github, for CICD Process.\u000ao Programming experience in CAPL, Python.\u000ao Experience in validation using, VT System HIL, CANoe, vTestStudio.\u000ao Experience of tools like Git, DOORS, JIRA, SVN, GitHub and PTC integrity\u000ao Understanding of ISO-26262 (Functional Safety), ASPICE Compliances\u000aPersonal Details :\u000aFATHER NAME : Ramchandra\u000aDOB : 18-sept-2000\u000aLanguages : English, Deutsch\u000aDeclarations:\u000aI hereby declare that information furnished above is true to the best of my knowledge.\u000a(Vaibhav)'),NULL);
INSERT INTO candidates VALUES(865,9,NULL,'Suram Sai Vignesh','suramsaivignesh@gmail.com','60',NULL,NULL,'Suram Sai Vignesh is an aspiring Software Engineer with 7 months of experience, proficient in HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Java, and PHP, demonstrating problem-solving and communication skills, and experience in responsive UI design.','pending','row_49','2025-11-20 14:25:16','2025-11-25 11:00:55','7730817730',NULL,NULL,unistr('Suram Sai Vignesh\u000aHyderabad | 7730817730 | suramsaivignesh@gmail.com\u000aObjective:\u000aAspiring Software Engineer with a strong foundation in electronics and communication engineering\u000aand hands-on experience in software development through academic projects and internship and an\u000aexperience of 7 months as Software Engineer. Eager to apply my programming skills and problem-\u000asolving abilities to contribute to innovative software solutions. Motivated to learn and grow within a\u000adynamic tech environment.\u000aTechnical Skills:\u000aProgramming Languages: Java, PHP\u000aWeb Technologies: HTML, CSS, JavaScript\u000aDatabases: MySQL , Oracle SQL\u000aTools & IDEs: Git, Visual Studio Code, Eclipse\u000aOperating Systems: Windows, Linux\u000aEducation:\u000aB.Tech in Electronics And Communication Engineering\u000aCMR Engineering College, Hyderabad, Telangana.\u000aGraduation: October, 2022\u000aIntermediate in MPC\u000aNarayana Junior College, Hyderabad, Telangana.\u000aCompletion: March, 2018\u000aSSC\u000aTelangana Model School Mirdoddi, Telangana.\u000aCompletion: April , 2016\u000aProjects:\u000aProject Title: Queue-Wise Dialing Implementation\u000aDescription:\u000a● Designed and implemented queue-wise dialing strategies for efficient call\u000adistribution in high-volume call center environments.\u000a● Configured ACD (Automatic Call Distribution) queues in Asterisk to optimize call\u000arouting, ensuring calls were directed to the most appropriate or available agents\u000abased on predefined rules (e.g., round-robin, least call, longest idle).\u000a● Managed and fine-tuned queue priorities to balance agent workloads, minimizing\u000await times and improving overall customer experience.\u000a● Developed customized scripts (AGI, PHP) for advanced queue management and call\u000aflow automation, integrating queue performance monitoring and real-time call\u000astatistics.\u000a\u000a● Analyzed and optimized queue performance using VoIP monitoring tools and real-\u000atime reporting, increasing efficiency by reducing average handling times and\u000amaximizing agent utilization.\u000a● Integrated queue-wise dialing with CRM systems for seamless call management and\u000acustomer data retrieval during active calls.\u000aExperience :\u000aSoftware Engineer\u000aDeepija Telecom Pvt Ltd, Hyderabad, Telangana\u000aDuration: March 2024- October 2024\u000a Developed and maintained web applications using Java and PHP, ensuring high\u000aperformance and scalability.\u000a Designed and implemented responsive user interfaces using HTML, CSS, and\u000aJavaScript.\u000a Collaborated with cross-functional teams to troubleshoot and resolve software\u000adefects.\u000a Managed and optimized Oracle SQL databases to support business operations.\u000a Utilized Git for version control, ensuring seamless collaboration across development\u000ateams.\u000a Assisted in gathering requirements and providing technical solutions to business\u000aneeds.\u000a'),NULL);
